'),(4,1,'Day 04: Srinagar - Katra','day414085124701408517795.jpg','This day morning after breakfast proceed by road to Katra, Katra is the starting point for the Vaishno Devi pilgrimage and A Base City of Maa Vaishno Devi Temple On arrive Katra Check in to the hotel, Overnight at hotel.','','This day morning after breakfast proceed by road to Katra, Katra is the starting point for the Vaishno Devi pilgrimage and A Base City of Maa Vaishno Devi Temple On arrive Katra Check in to the hotel, Overnight at hotel.','229578',1,'2014-08-20 10:57:50'),(5,1,'Day 05: Katra','day514085125091408517874.jpg','This Day Morning After breakfast, proceed for Mata Vaishno Devi Darshan. Heli / Poni/ Horse ride from Katra to Mata Vaishno Devi Darshan (own). After darshan, back to Katra overnight stay at the hotel.','','This Day Morning After breakfast, proceed for Mata Vaishno Devi Darshan. Heli / Poni/ Horse ride from Katra to Mata Vaishno Devi Darshan (own). After darshan, back to Katra overnight stay at the hotel.','494658',1,'2014-08-20 10:58:29'),(6,1,'Day 06: Katra - Jammu - Hyderabad','day614085125451408517938.jpg','This day morning after breakfast we will depart you to Jammu Airport for back to home.','','This day morning after breakfast we will depart you to Jammu Airport for back to home.','993123',1,'2014-08-20 10:59:05'),(7,11,'Day 1 :Delhi - Shimla (343 kms / 7-8 hrs)','Day11408515983.jpg','Arrive Delhi & Transfer  by road to Shimla former summer capital of British India & now a capital of Himachal Pradesh, set amidst the snow capped shivalik mountain ranges offering some stunning views of the mighty Himalayas, proceed to your hotel and rest of the day is at leisure, overnight at the hotel','','Arrive Delhi & Transfer  by road to Shimla former summer capital of British India & now a capital of Himachal Pradesh, set amidst the snow capped shivalik mountain ranges offering some stunning views of the mighty Himalayas, proceed to your hotel and rest of the day is at leisure, overnight at the hotel','514238',1,'2014-08-20 11:56:23'),(8,11,'Day 2 :Shimla','Day21408516384.jpg','This morning you will visit the Kufri situated at an altitude of 2500 meters just an hours drive from Shimla and a very popular ski resort during the winter months. Later this afternoon take a walking tour of Shimla, visit the Jakoo hills which offers panoramic vies of the Shimla town, proceed to the Vice regal lodge and later walk down the Mall road, overnight at the hotel\r\n','','This morning you will visit the Kufri situated at an altitude of 2500 meters just an hours drive from Shimla and a very popular ski resort during the winter months. Later this afternoon take a walking tour of Shimla, visit the Jakoo hills which offers panoramic vies of the Shimla town, proceed to the Vice regal lodge and later walk down the Mall road, overnight at the hotel\r\n','481542',1,'2014-08-20 12:03:04'),(9,11,'Day 3 : Shimla - Manali (260 kms / 7- 8 hrs)','Day31408516726.jpg','Today you will proceed by road to Manali a picture-perfect hill resort at an altitude of 1,929 metres. Set amidst pine-clad mountains, which gradually close in on both sides of the Beas and nestling in their shade, as though carved out of primeval forest, is a scattered hamlet, which comprises this picturesque summer resort. Proceed to your hotel. Rest of the evening is at leisure, overnight at the hotel','','Today you will proceed by road to Manali a picture-perfect hill resort at an altitude of 1,929 metres. Set amidst pine-clad mountains, which gradually close in on both sides of the Beas and nestling in their shade, as though carved out of primeval forest, is a scattered hamlet, which comprises this picturesque summer resort. Proceed to your hotel. Rest of the evening is at leisure, overnight at the hotel','697199',1,'2014-08-20 12:08:46'),(10,11,'Day 4: Manali','Day41408517023.jpg','This morning you will visit the Solang Valley, which offers fine views of glaciers and snow, capped peaks. A place not to be missed is Rohtang Pass, 51 km from Manali at an altitude of 3978 meters (subject to weather conditions). In the Evening proceed for a walking tour of Manali, visit the 450 years old temple dedicated to Hadimba Devi, which has some excellent woodcarving. Visit the Tibetan Monastery and a handicraft center. Rest of the day at leisure OR optionally you may walk to nearby picturesque village of Vashisht known for hot sulphur springs. Overnight at the hotel','','This morning you will visit the Solang Valley, which offers fine views of glaciers and snow, capped peaks. A place not to be missed is Rohtang Pass, 51 km from Manali at an altitude of 3978 meters (subject to weather conditions). In the Evening proceed for a walking tour of Manali, visit the 450 years old temple dedicated to Hadimba Devi, which has some excellent woodcarving. Visit the Tibetan Monastery and a handicraft center. Rest of the day at leisure OR optionally you may walk to nearby picturesque village of Vashisht known for hot sulphur springs. Overnight at the hotel','254508',1,'2014-08-20 12:13:43'),(11,11,'Day 5 :	 Manali-Chandigarh(270 Km/6-7 Hrs)','Day51408517413.jpg','This Day After Breakfast  Proceed to Chandigarh The Joint Capital of Punjab and Haryana Arrive  Chandigarh Check in to Hotel  Later Afternoon visit to Rock Garden and Rose Garden in the Evening Boating at Sukuna Lake Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel.','','This Day After Breakfast  Proceed to Chandigarh The Joint Capital of Punjab and Haryana Arrive  Chandigarh Check in to Hotel  Later Afternoon visit to Rock Garden and Rose Garden in the Evening Boating at Sukuna Lake Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel.','237424',1,'2014-08-20 12:20:13'),(12,11,'Day 6 :Chandigarh - Depart to Delhi (250 kms/4-5 hrs)','Day61408517709.jpg','This day after breakfast we will Depart to you Delhi Rly stn /Airport.','','This day after breakfast we will Depart to you Delhi Rly stn /Airport.','333213',1,'2014-08-20 12:25:09'),(14,2,'Day 1 : Srinagar','day11409635627.jpg','Arrive  Srinagar, a Lake city of Kashmir, located in the heart of the Kashmir valley at an altitude of 1,730 m above sea level, famous for its lakes dotted with Shikaras,  and the Mughal Gardens. Transfer to hotel. This afternoon visit the world famous Mughal gardens built by Emperor Jehangir. Enjoy a <b><i>Shikara ride</i></b> on the picturesque Dal lake. Back to Hotel Overnight at House Boat.','','Arrive  Srinagar, a Lake city of Kashmir, located in the heart of the Kashmir valley at an altitude of 1,730 m above sea level, famous for its lakes dotted with Shikaras,  and the Mughal Gardens. Transfer to hotel. This afternoon visit the world famous Mughal gardens built by Emperor Jehangir. Enjoy a <b><i>Shikara ride</i></b> on the picturesque Dal lake. Back to Hotel Overnight at House Boat.','219142',1,'2014-09-02 10:57:07'),(13,15,'Day 01 : Hyderabad City tour','charminar_hyderabad1408952985.jpg','07:00 Am: Chandanagar <br>\r\n07:30 Am: Kukatpally<br>\r\n08:00 Am : Hi-Tech City Cyber Tower<br>\r\n08:30 Am: Lakidaka pool<br>\r\nOnward Journey  to City Tour <br>\r\n\r\nEnd of Tour  06:00Pm \r\n','','07:00 Am: Chandanagar <br>\r\n07:30 Am: Kukatpally<br>\r\n08:00 Am : Hi-Tech City Cyber Tower<br>\r\n08:30 Am: Lakidaka pool<br>\r\nOnward Journey  to City Tour <br>\r\n\r\nEnd of Tour  06:00Pm \r\n','949110',1,'2014-08-25 13:19:45'),(15,2,'Day 2 : Srinagar - Gulmarg - Srinagar (55 kms/1-2 hrs one way)','day21409635690.jpg','This morning proceed for a full day excursion to Gulmarg, a Meadow of Flowers situated at an altitude of 2730 meters, and a famous ski resort duringthe winters. Enjoy leisurely walks on the lush green meadows of flowers with a backdrop of the snow capped mountains OR enjoy an optional Gondola ride (Cable Car), Khilanmarg . Back to Hotel Over night at Hotel.','','This morning proceed for a full day excursion to Gulmarg, a Meadow of Flowers situated at an altitude of 2730 meters, and a famous ski resort duringthe winters. Enjoy leisurely walks on the lush green meadows of flowers with a backdrop of the snow capped mountains OR enjoy an optional Gondola ride (Cable Car), Khilanmarg . Back to Hotel Over night at Hotel.','308774',1,'2014-09-02 10:58:10'),(16,2,'Day 3 : Srinagar - Pahalgam - SriNagar (95 kms / 3 - 4 hrs)','day31409635783.jpg','Today you will be transferred by road to Pahalgam, the Valley of Shepherds - Situated at the confluence of the streams flowing from Sheshnag Lake and the Lidder river, situated at 2,130 m.   day free to explore Pahalgam on your won or take an optional visit to chandanwari  or Aru for a magnificent view of Lidder Valley. Overnight at the hotel.\r\n','','Today you will be transferred by road to Pahalgam, the Valley of Shepherds - Situated at the confluence of the streams flowing from Sheshnag Lake and the Lidder river, situated at 2,130 m.   day free to explore Pahalgam on your won or take an optional visit to chandanwari  or Aru for a magnificent view of Lidder Valley. Overnight at the hotel.','139257',1,'2014-09-02 10:59:43'),(17,2,'Day 4  :  Srinagar - Katra','day41409635825.jpg','This day after B/fast we will Transferred By road to Katra, A Base City of Maa Viashnodevi Temple On arrive Katra Check in to Hotel ,Overnight At Hotel.','','This day after B/fast we will Transferred By road to Katra, A Base City of Maa Viashnodevi Temple On arrive Katra Check in to Hotel ,Overnight At Hotel.','188383',1,'2014-09-02 11:00:25'),(18,2,'Day 5  :  Katra ','day51409635853.jpg','This day after Breakfast you will trekking / By Heli (on your own) to Maa Vaishnodevi Temple for Pooja And Dharshan  Back to Hotel Overnight   at Katra.','','This day after Breakfast you will trekking / By Heli (on your own) to Maa Vaishnodevi Temple for Pooja And Dharshan  Back to Hotel Overnight   at Katra.','636184',1,'2014-09-02 11:00:53'),(19,2,'Day 6  :  Katra-Depart to Jammu Airport','day61409635883.jpg','This Morning We will Depart to you Jammu Airport for Catch Flight Back to Home.','','This Morning We will Depart to you Jammu Airport for Catch Flight Back to Home.','799954',1,'2014-09-02 11:01:23'),(20,3,'Day	01: Hyderabad - Delhi - Haridwar (230kms/7 Hrs)','day11409636656.jpg','This Day Catch Flight from RAJIV GANDHI INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT, Hyderabad for Onward Journey to Delhi! you will be met by an SVR TRAVELS INDIA PVT LTD representative On arrival at New Delhi Airport.Board the Coach (08:30 AM) and drive to Haridwar, Arrive Haridwar Check in the hotel later evening proceed to Hari ki Pauri for Ganga Aarti at Ganga Ghat. Back to hotel Overnight at hotel','','This Day Catch Flight from RAJIV GANDHI INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT, Hyderabad for Onward Journey to Delhi! you will be met by an SVR TRAVELS INDIA PVT LTD representative On arrival at New Delhi Airport.Board the Coach (08:30 AM) and drive to Haridwar, Arrive Haridwar Check in the hotel later evening proceed to Hari ki Pauri for Ganga Aarti at Ganga Ghat. Back to hotel Overnight at hotel','374409',1,'2014-09-02 11:14:16'),(21,3,'Day 02:  Haridwar  - Rishikesh - Barkot(200kms/7 hrs)','day21409636683.jpg','Today Morning after breakfast proceeds for Sightseeing which covers Shivananda Ashram, Ram Jhoola, Swarg Ashram, Geeta Ashram, Laxman Jhoola, After lunch proceeds to Barkot, via Dehradun & Mussoorie. En- route visit Kempty Fall and enjoy the beauty of Himalayas, later drive straight to Barkot for night stay.','','Today Morning after breakfast proceeds for Sightseeing which covers Shivananda Ashram, Ram Jhoola, Swarg Ashram, Geeta Ashram, Laxman Jhoola, After lunch proceeds to Barkot, via Dehradun & Mussoorie. En- route visit Kempty Fall and enjoy the beauty of Himalayas, later drive straight to Barkot for night stay.','342307',1,'2014-09-02 11:14:43'),(22,3,'Day 03:  Barkot  - Yamunotri  - Barkot (45 Kms road/ 6kms Trek)','day31409636737.jpg','Drive to Jankichatti, the trek starts from here to Yamunotri (6kms). On arrival leave the vehicle and start to ascend on trek route either by walk or pony/Doli (at own cost). On arrival at Yamunotri purchase, Prasad forms local small shops, then proceed to holy dip in natural hot water spring or in river Yamuna (icy cold water). One can cook rice in \"Surya Kund\" (hot water spring), dipping in a muslin cloth and take cooked rice home as \"Prasadam\". Pooja can be offered to mythological \"Divya Shila\". Take blessings of Mata Yamuna and trek down to Jankichatti. Later drive back to Barkot for night stay.\r\n<font color=\"#199FCE\"><b>Approx. charges for Pony: - Rs. 1000 - 1500/- Per Person</b></font><br>\r\n<font color=\"#199FCE\"><b>Approx. charges for Doli : - Rs. 4000 - 4500/- Per Person</b></font>','','Drive to Jankichatti, the trek starts from here to Yamunotri (6kms). On arrival leave the vehicle and start to ascend on trek route either by walk or pony/Doli (at own cost). On arrival at Yamunotri purchase, Prasad forms local small shops, then proceed to holy dip in natural hot water spring or in river Yamuna (icy cold water). One can cook rice in \"Surya Kund\" (hot water spring), dipping in a muslin cloth and take cooked rice home as \"Prasadam\". Pooja can be offered to mythological \"Divya Shila\". Take blessings of Mata Yamuna and trek down to Jankichatti. Later drive back to Barkot for night stay.\r\n<font color=\"#199FCE\"><b>Approx. charges for Pony: - Rs. 1000 - 1500/- Per Person</b></font>','482194',1,'2014-09-02 11:15:37'),(23,3,'Day 04: Barkot - Uttarkashi(90kms/4hrs)','day41409636768.jpg','Morning departs to Uttarkashi, on arrival check in at a hotel, later visit famous Kashi Vishwanath temple at Uttarkashi. Overnight stay at a hotel.','','Morning departs to Uttarkashi, on arrival check in at a hotel, later visit famous Kashi Vishwanath temple at Uttarkashi. Overnight stay at a hotel.','189890',1,'2014-09-02 11:16:08'),(24,3,'Day 05:  Uttarkashi Gangotri - Uttarkashi(24kms/2hrs)','char1547023942.jpg','Morning proceeds to Gangotri (3048 mts), en -route enjoy the drive parallel to Bhagirathi River and the most magnificent view of the Himalayas. On arrival, Gangotri has a holy dip in river Bhagirathi (icy cold water). Perform Pooja and Hindu rites at the bank of a river. Then proceed to darshan, of Mata Ganga, Lord Shiva, Hanuman, Vinayaka and Bhagirath-Maharaj, have blessings and return back to Uttarkashi. Overnight stay at Uttarkashi.','','Morning proceeds to Gangotri (3048 mts), en -route enjoy the drive parallel to Bhagirathi River and the most magnificent view of the Himalayas. On arrival, Gangotri has a holy dip in river Bhagirathi (icy cold water). Perform Pooja and Hindu rites at the bank of a river. Then proceed to darshan, of Mata Ganga, Lord Shiva, Hanuman, Vinayaka and Bhagirath-Maharaj, have blessings and return back to Uttarkashi. Overnight stay at Uttarkashi.\r\n\r\nApprox. charges for Pony: - Rs. 800 - 1200/- Per Person\r\nApprox. charges for Doli: - Rs. 2500 - 3500/- Per Person\r\nHelicopter Fare-- Rs.8000/- per person Up to 90 Kg.(Rate May Be Change )','627484',1,'2014-09-02 11:16:45'),(25,3,'Day 06:  Uttarkashi - Srinagar(205kms/ 8hrs)','day61409636834.jpg','Morning departs to Srinagar. En-route visit word famous India&#39;s the biggest Dam \"Tehri Dam\" later drive to Srinagar. On arrival check-in to the hotel, night stays at Srinagar.','','Morning departs to Srinagar. En-route visit word famous India&#39;s the biggest Dam \"Tehri Dam\" later drive to Srinagar. On arrival check-in to the hotel, night stays at Srinagar.','248737',1,'2014-09-02 11:17:14'),(26,3,'Day 07:  Srinagar - Sitapur(80kms/4 Hrs)','day71409636870.jpg','Morning drive to Sitapur or Phata. En-route visit Dhari Devi temple & Rudraprayag (the confluence point of 2 Holy rivers - Alaknanda and Mandakini), later drive to Guptkashi & visit Shri Kashi Viswanath Temple (Ardhanariswar Temple) Later do Registration for visiting Kedarnath, overnight stay at Hotel.\r\n\r\nRudraprayag: It is the confluence of river Mandakini and Alaknanda, Rudranath, Temple & Narad Silla.\r\n','','Morning drive to Sitapur or Phata. En-route visit Dhari Devi temple & Rudraprayag (the confluence point of 2 Holy rivers - Alaknanda and Mandakini), later drive to Guptkashi & visit Shri Kashi Viswanath Temple (Ardhanariswar Temple) Later do Registration for visiting Kedarnath, overnight stay at Hotel.\r\n\r\nRudraprayag: It is the confluence of river Mandakini and Alaknanda, Rudranath, Temple & Narad Silla.\r\n','192479',1,'2014-09-02 11:17:50'),(27,3,'Day 08:  Sitapur - Kedarnath - Sitapur (18 kms Trek)','day81409637014.jpg','Early morning drive to Sonprayag/ Phata (for trek route or helipad)trek starts from here to Kedarnath (3584 mts) on foot or Heli/doli/pony (at own cost). Tour members should carry personal medicines, heavy woollen, toiletries and clothes. After performing Pooja & Darshan of Shri Kedarnath Ji return to Gaurikund and then to Sitapur. Overnight stay at Hotel.\r\n<br>\r\n<font color=\"#199FCE\"><b>Approx. charges for Pony: - Rs. 1000 - 1500/- Per Person</b></font><br>\r\n<font color=\"#199FCE\"><b>Approx. charges for Doli : - Rs. 4000 - 4500/- Per Person</b></font>\r\n<font color=\"#199FCE\"><b>\r\n<br>\r\nApprox. charges for Heli : - Rs. 4000 - 4500/- Per Person</b>','','Early morning drive to Sonprayag/ Phata (for trek route or helipad)trek starts from here to Kedarnath (3584 mts) on foot or Heli/doli/pony (at own cost). Tour members should carry personal medicines, heavy woollen, toiletries and clothes. After performing Pooja & Darshan of Shri Kedarnath Ji return to Gaurikund and then to Sitapur. Overnight stay at Hotel.','395531',1,'2014-09-02 11:20:14'),(28,3,'Day 09: Sitapur  - Badrinath(230 kms / 9 Hrs)','day91409637062.JPG','Morning After breakfast transfer to Badrinath, en-route visit Karanprayag, Nandprayag, Vishnu Prayag, & Joshimath (Narshimha Temple) on arrival check in at a hotel, in the evening visit Badrinath temple, overnight stay at a hotel.','','Morning After breakfast transfer to Badrinath, en-route visit Karanprayag, Nandprayag, Vishnu Prayag, & Joshimath (Narshimha Temple) on arrival check in at a hotel, in the evening visit Badrinath temple, overnight stay at a hotel.','646715',1,'2014-09-02 11:21:02'),(29,3,'Day 10:  Badrinath - Pipalkoti(80kms/4 hrs)','day101409637103.JPG','Morning visit temple after a holy dip in Taptkund. Proceed through a colorful entrance of the temple have Darshan of Badrivishal along with Ganesh, Kubera, Garuda, Narada, Udhhav, Nar & Narayan. Also see other small temples inside the temple compound i.e. Laxmimata, Nar-Narayana, Hanuman, Ghantakarn and Kaamdhenu. One can get \"Char-namirt\"(abhishekamjal) inside a compound. Brahamakapal is significant for Pinddam Shraddh of ancestors (Pitrus), one can perform right here. Later a visit of Mana Village (India&#8223;s the last village towards Indo-Tibetan border), which includes Vyasa Gufa, Ganesh Gufa, Bhimpul, Saraswati river etc, In the evening transfer to Pipalkoti, Overnight stay at Pipalkot','','Morning visit temple after a holy dip in Taptkund. Proceed through a colorful entrance of the temple have Darshan of Badrivishal along with Ganesh, Kubera, Garuda, Narada, Udhhav, Nar & Narayan. Also see other small temples inside the temple compound i.e. Laxmimata, Nar-Narayana, Hanuman, Ghantakarn and Kaamdhenu. One can get \"Char-namirt\"(abhishekamjal) inside a compound. Brahamakapal is significant for Pinddam Shraddh of ancestors (Pitrus), one can perform right here. Later a visit of Mana Village (India&#8223;s the last village towards Indo-Tibetan border), which includes Vyasa Gufa, Ganesh Gufa, Bhimpul, Saraswati river etc, In the evening transfer to Pipalkoti, Overnight stay at Pipalkot','543439',1,'2014-09-02 11:21:43'),(30,3,'Day 11: Pipalkoti - Haridwar(250kms/6-7 hrs)','day111409637186.jpg','Morning after transfer to Haridwar, en-route visit Devprayag the confluence of Alaknanda and Bhagirathi. Here the onwards downstream river is called the Ganges, later transfer to Haridwar, on arrival proceed to perform ritualistic bathi