orld famous\r\nMughal gardens built by Emperor\r\nJehangir. Enjoy a Shikara ride on the\r\npicturesque Dal lake. Overnight on\r\nboard House Boat.','','','882421',1,'2014-09-29 19:32:28'),(515,51,'Day 02 : Srinagar - Pahalgam- Srinagar (94 kms/3 -4 hrs One way )','Day21411999397.jpg','Today you will be transferred by road\r\nto Pahalgam, the Valley of Shepherds -\r\nSituated at the confluence of the\r\nstreams flowing from Sheshnag Lake\r\nand the Lidder river, situated at 2,130\r\nm. Arrive may visit to chandanwari or\r\nAru for a magnificent view of Lidder\r\nValley on your Own. Back to Hotel\r\nOvernight at Hotel','','','385733',1,'2014-09-29 19:33:17'),(516,51,'Day 03 : Pahalgam - Gulmarg-Srinagar (55 kms / 1-2 hrs one way)','Day31411999448.jpg','This morning proceed for a full day\r\nexcursion to Gulmarg, a Meadow of\r\nFlowers situated at an altitude of 2730\r\nmeters, and a famous ski resort during\r\nthe winters. Enjoy leisurely walks on\r\nthe lush green meadows of flowers with\r\na backdrop of the snow capped\r\nmountains OR enjoy an optional\r\nGondola ride (Cable Car), Khilanmarg .\r\nBack to Srinagar Overnight at Srinagar.','','','765065',1,'2014-09-29 19:34:08'),(517,51,'Day 04 : Srinagar-Sonemarg-Srinagar(84 Km/3-4 Hrs)','Day41411999611.jpg','Drive to Sonamarg through the Sindh Valley which presents yet another spectacular facet of countryside in Kashmir. Situated at an altitude of 2730 m, Sonamarg (&#39;The meadow of gold&#39;) has, as its backdrop, snowy mountains against a cerulean sky. Optionally visit Thajiwas glacier, a major local attraction during the summer months. Evening drive back to Srinagar. Overnight on board the Houseboat/Hotel','','Drive to Sonamarg through the Sindh Valley which presents yet another spectacular facet of countryside in Kashmir. Situated at an altitude of 2730 m, Sonamarg (&#39;The meadow of gold&#39;) has, as its backdrop, snowy mountains against a cerulean sky. Optionally visit Thajiwas glacier, a major local attraction during the summer months. Evening drive back to Srinagar. Overnight on board the Houseboat/Hotel','936912',1,'2014-09-29 19:36:51'),(518,62,'Day 01 : Arrive Gangtok (90 kms / 2-3 hrs)','Day1_at_Nathula-Pass1412000018.JPG','Arrive This morning you will be transferred by road to Gangtok, is literally the “lofty hill” set amidst the clouds and mists of the splendorous Himalayas and is a gateway to Sikkim.Proceed to your hotel and rest\r\nof the day at leisure. Overnight at the hotel.\r\n','','','237084',1,'2014-09-29 19:43:38'),(519,62,'Day 02 :  Gangtok','Day2_at_-Baba-Mandir1412000522.jpg','This morning proceed on an excursion to Baba Mandir, dedicated to a old soldier of Indian Army, later visit picturesque Tsomgo lake, a holy lake worshipped by the Sikkimese. Enjoy an optional yak ride around the lake. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','532520',1,'2014-09-29 19:46:16'),(520,62,'Day 03 : Gangtok - Lachung (117Kms/5 - 6 Hrs)','Day3_at_Lachung1412000642.jpg','Today you will drive to Lachung (small pass) situated at an height of 8,610 feet, one of the most exquisite villages in the valleys of North Sikkim. With resplendent snow-capped mountains, dazzling waterfalls and sparkling streams. Enroute to Lachung you will stop to visit the Phodong Monastery. The original monastery has been rebuilt and is today one of the most beautiful monasteries in Sikkim. It possesses the old mural paintings and has around 260 monks.. Arrive and proceed to your hotel. Evening at leisure to explore this beautiful Himalayan village on your own. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','889991',1,'2014-09-29 19:54:02'),(521,62,'Day 04 : Lachung ','Day4_Yumthang-Valley1412000726.jpg','This morning visit to Yumthang Valley, situated at an altitude of about 11,800 ft. It is covered with rhododendron shrubs and trees of various species. The valley is well known for its hot springs, you will visit the Hot Spring and Singba Rhododendron Sanctuary. Later visit Lachung Monastery. Evening is at leisure. Overnight at the hotel.\r\n','','','218390',1,'2014-09-29 19:55:26'),(522,62,'Day 05 : Lachung - Gangtok','Day5_at_leaure1412000774.jpg','In the morning you will be transferred back to Gangtok  . Proceed to your hotel and rest of the day is at leisure for shopping and individual activities. Overnight at the hotel.\r\n','','','362555',1,'2014-09-29 19:56:14'),(523,62,'Day 06 :  Gangtok-Pelling(120 km/4-5 hrs)','Day6_at_Khangchendzonga1412000868.jpg','Today you will be transferred to Pelling. A placid Pelling pulls most of the visitors for its representative status in history, nature and culture of the state. Situated at an altitude of 6,800 ft, famous for its magnificent view of the snow-capped mountains of Khangchendzonga. Arrive and proceed to your hotel, Later Afternoon you will visit Pemayangtse monastery, situated on the back drop of the Eastern Himalayas, built in 17th Century AD, which houses several religious images and other objects of worship, most of which are precious because of their ancientness. Later you will visit tranquil Khecheopalri Lake, surrounded by blooming forest and is considered as one of the sacred lakes of Sikkim both by the Buddhist and the Hindus. Back to Hotel Overnight at Pelling Hotel.\r\n','','','646155',1,'2014-09-29 19:57:48'),(524,62,'Day 07  :  Pelling- Darjeeling','Day7_at_Mirik-Lake1412000974.jpg','This day after Breakfast we will transfer to Darjeeling. Enroute you will visit beautiful Mirik Lake. Arrive and proceed to your hotel. Overnight at thehotel.\r\n','','','596518',1,'2014-09-29 19:59:34'),(525,62,'Day 08 :  Darjeeling ','Day8_at_-Batasia-loop1412001033.jpg','Early morning (0330 hrs) visit Tiger Hills to witness the spectacular sunrise over the Kanchanjunga mountains. On the return visit the famous Ghoom Monastery and Batasia loop. This afternoon visit the Himalayan Mountaineering Institute, the Himalayan Zoo and the Botanical Gardens. At the end of the tour visit the Tibetan Handicraft Center and drive past Darjeeling Tea G