oria Palace, Kalighat in the Evening free for Leisure Optional you may shopping at  Famous Park Street which is Adjacent from your Hotel  Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel. \r\n','','','578688',1,'2014-09-29 20:43:53'),(546,66,'Day 02 : Kolkata- Dimapur-Kohima ','Day21412003667.JPG','Drive to Dimapur the erstwhile capital of the Kacheri rulers. It is one of the oldest town of Nagaland. Meet and Greet transferred Kohima The Capital of Nagaland Check in to Hotel Overnight at Hotel. \r\n','','','772214',1,'2014-09-29 20:44:27'),(547,66,'Day 03 : Kohima ','Day31412003729.jpg','This morning drive to Kohima, check into hotel, Afternoon visit The State Museum, located at Bayani hill Kohima, it gives you a peep into the various aspects of Naga Culture also visit the WW II Cemetery, nestled in heart of Kohima town. Overnight in Hotel. \r\n','','','101510',1,'2014-09-29 20:45:29'),(548,66,'Day 04 : Kohima ','Day41412003802.jpg','After breakfast Proceed to Kepfiizha (Kigwema village) Dimori Cove Guest house for lunch. After lunch visit nearby Angami village of Jakhama, Drive to Touphema Village Resort (41 \r\nkms from Kohima) run by Angami Naga village community. Enjoy cultural presentation by village folks. Overnight at Touphema Tourist village, resort. \r\n','','','135717',1,'2014-09-29 20:46:42'),(549,66,'Day 05 : Kohima - Dimapur-Kolkata','Day51412003918.jpg','This After Breakfast we will Depart to Dimapur Airport for Back to Kolkata. Arrive Kolkata Airport Meet and Greet Proceed for Sightseeing of Dakshineshwar Temple and Science Museum Overnight at Kolkata \r\n','','','801051',1,'2014-09-29 20:48:38'),(550,66,'Day 06 : Depart to Kolkata Airport','Day61412003963.jpg','This Day we will Depart to Kolkata Airport for Back to Home \r\n','','','838616',1,'2014-09-29 20:49:23'),(551,67,'Day 01 : Arrive Kolkata','Day11412004086.jpg','On arrive at Kolkata Meet and Greet Check in to Hotel After Fresh up Proceed for Sightseeing of  Howrah Bridge, Victoria Palace, Kalighat in the Evening free for Leisure Optional you may shopping at  Famous Park Street which is Adjacent from your Hotel  Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel. \r\n','','','429754',1,'2014-09-29 20:51:26'),(552,67,'Day 2 : Kolkata-Agartala','Day21412004133.jpg','Pick up from agartala airport. After Lunch Proceed to Kamlasaagar Kali Temple. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n','','','109952',1,'2014-09-29 20:52:13'),(553,67,'Day 3 : Agartala-Udaipur-Neer Mahal-Agartala','Day31412004160.jpg','Early morning breakfast. Visit Udaipur Mata Kali Temple, Tepania Eco Park and Neer Mahal. Return to hotel and have lunch. \r\nIn the evening, go for Akhaura Check Post ( Indo – Bangla Border ) And local temple visits. Overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n','','','929556',1,'2014-09-29 20:52:40'),(554,67,'Day 04 : Depart to Agartala Airport','Day41412004206.jpg','Have breakfast and drop to airport with fond memories of Agartala .\r\n','','','736697',1,'2014-09-29 20:53:26'),(555,68,'Day 01: Arrive Aizawl','Day11412004288.jpg','Meeting upon arrival and transfer to hotel.\r\nAizawl: Aizawl, the state Capital of Mizoram is located at an altitude of 4000 feet above sea level. Surrounded on the east by the deep green valley of river Tlawng and protected by beautiful high hills of Durtlang on the north, it is an ideal hill station for those looking for some fresh air and solitude. Evening free to explore the city by your own. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','898469',1,'2014-09-29 20:54:48'),(556,68,'Day 02 : Aizawl','Day21412004361.jpg','Morning after breakfast full day city tour visiting:<br>\r\n<b>Bara Bazar:</b> It is the most important shopping hub with stalls selling garments, and other commodities. Here the people can be seen in their traditional costumes selling products from farms and homesteads including river crabs with little wicker baskets. <br>\r\n<b>Luangmual Handicarfts Centre:</b> 7 Kms away from Aizaul it takes half an hour to reach by car. The &#39;Khumbeu&#39; ceremonial bamboo hat is made here using waterproof &#39;hnahthial&#39; leaves.\r\n<br>\r\n<b>Mizoram State Museum: </b>This museum is situated at Mc Donald Hill in the town center. it is having an interesting collection of historical relics, ancient costumes and traditional implements. \r\n(Open Monday - Friday from 9:00 A.M to 5 PM. Saturday 9 AM to 1 PM)\r\n<br>\r\n<b>Durtlang Hills: </b>These beautiful, craggy hills offer the breathtaking view of Aizawl.\r\n <br>\r\n<b>Mini Zoo: </b>Home to species of animals and birds found only in the hills of Mizoram\r\nBerawtlang Tourist Complex: This is a recreational center situated 7 kms away from Aizawl City. It offers the facilities of Restaurant as well as Tourist Cottages.<br>\r\nOvernight at hotel.','','','286937',1,'2014-09-29 20:56:01'),(557,68,'Day 03: Aizwal / Tamdil / Aizawl (85 Kms, 2 hrs drive)','Day31412004858.jpg','Morning after breakfast full day excursion for Tamdil lake.\r\n<br><b>Tamdil Lake: </b>85 kms from Aizawl, Tamdil is the largest natural lake in Mizoram surrounded by cool virgin forests. It is an ideal picnic spot for the tourists with the facilities of boating and fishing and also the Tourist lodge for those who wish to spend a night or two to enjoy the serenity of the place.\r\nLater return to Aizawl.\r\nOvernight at hotel.\r\n','','','903629',1,'2014-09-29 21:04:18'),(558,68,'Day 04: Aizawl / Champhai','Day41412004929.jpg','Morning after breakfast depart for Champhai.\r\n<br>\r\n<b>Champhai: </b>Champhai is a busy commercial town and a developing venue for Indo-Myanmar border trade and ideal place for marketing all kinds of goods. It is an important agriculture and sericulture centre and its surroundings present the tourist with a view of the hills of Myanmar. 5 km away from Champhai is the Ruantlang village where glimpses of the ancestral way of life of the Mizos can still be seen.\r\nOvernight at Champhai tourist lodge.\r\n','','','517086',1,'2014-09-29 21:05:29'),(559,68,'Day 05 : Champhai /Depart to  Aizawl Airport(180 Km/4-5 Hrs)','Day51412004965.jpg','Morning after breakfast in time transfer to airport for the onward destination.\r\nTour ends.\r\n','','','707123',1,'2014-09-29 21:06:05'),(560,69,'Day 01 : Arrive Kolkata','Day11412005068.jpg','On arrive at Kolkata Meet and Greet Check in to Hotel After Fresh up Proceed for Sightseeing of  Howrah Bridge, Victoria Palace, Kalighat in the Evening free for Leisure Optional you may shopping at  Famous Park Street which is Adjacent from your Hotel  Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel. \r\n','','','813814',1,'2014-09-29 21:07:48'),(561,69,'Day 02 : Arrive Imphal','Day21412005164.jpg','Meeting upon arrival and transfer to hotel.<br>\r\nAfternoon visit:<br>\r\n<b>Shree Shree Govindajee Temple: </b>This symbolic temple in Imphal adjoining the palace of the former rulers of Manipur, is a historic centre for Vaisnava culture. It is a simple and beautiful structure with gold domes, a paved court and a large, raised congregation hall. The main deity of the Temple is The presiding deity in the centre is flanked by idols of Radha Govinda, Balaram and Krishna on one side and Jagannath, Balabhadra and Subhadra on the other.<br>\r\n<b>Khwairamband Bazaar: </b>One of the main attraction of Imphal is the Khwairamband Bazaar. What makes this market different is that it is run by women. Split into two sections on either side of the road, it has tribal women clad in colorful, traditional attire, selling everything from hand-woven shawls, skirts, vessels, mugs and mats to fish, lotus, oranges and orange-flavored honey. And if you wander in the quaint by lanes around the market, you will get a glimpse of Manipur&#39;s customs and traditions.\r\nKhonghampat Orchidarium: There is the Khonghampat Orchidarium that has more than a hundred rare varieties of orchids. The best time to visit the orchidarium is in the months of April and May when the orchids are in full bloom.<br>\r\nOvernight at hotel.\r\n','','','589293',1,'2014-09-29 21:09:24'),(562,69,'Day 03: Imphal','Day31412005296.jpg','Morning after breakfast full day excursion around Imphal visiting:\r\n<br>\r\n<b>Loktak Lake and Sendra Island: </b>Located 48 kms from Imphal this beautiful lake is resemble like a miniature inland sea. The government had built a Tourist Bungalow for the comfort of the tourists. From the nearby Sendra island, visitors can get a bird&#39;s eye view of this huge and beautiful stretch of water and the life on it, the fisherman and their families who live in neat huts on its shores and anticipating their watery environment by casting their nets on it, harvesting it for the water chestnut known as Heikak, and even building their houses on the islands of floating weed that dart around the lake.<br>\r\n\r\n<b>Keibul Lamjao National Park: </b>53 kms. from Imphal and on the sharing the border with Loktak Lake, Keibul Lamjao National Park is the last natural habitat of the endangered marsh-dwelling brow-antlered deer of Manipur called \"Sangai\". It is the only floating national park in the world which is composed of large masses of floating weed (called \"Phumdi\" in local dialect). These phumdi unseemingly can suport a lot of weight.\r\n','','','837493',1,'2014-09-29 21:11:36'),(563,69,'Day 04 : Imphal Depart','Day41412005332.jpg','Morning after breakfast in time transfer to airport for the onward destination.\r\nTour ends.\r\n','','','630035',1,'2014-09-29 21:12:12'),(564,108,'Day 01 : Arrive Port Blair','Day1-120x1001419659595.jpg','Arrive  Veer Savarkar International Airport, Port Blair, commonly known as Port Blair Airport located 2 km (1.2 mi) south of  Port Blair and is the main airport of the Andaman and   Nicobar Islands of India. It is named after the Indian freedom  fighter \"Vinayak Damodar Savarkar\" our delegate will escort you for a comfortable Check-In.  After lunch:- \r\nLocal Excursion : Chatham Saw mill, Forest Museum, Samudrika Naval Marine Museum, Anthropological Museum, Cellular Jail\r\nCarbyn&#39;s Cove 	: (7 Kms from Port Blair - a coconut palm fringed beach, ideal for swimming, sun-basking & bathing) Sound & Light Show - where the heroic saga of the Indian freedom struggle is brought alive Back to Hotel. Overnight at Hotel shompen/Is lander Inn/Classic Regency/Hotel Drift wood','','','106823',1,'2014-12-27 11:23:15'),(565,108,'Day 02:Port Blair-Have Lock Island','Day2-120x1001419659819.jpg','Early morning departure by inter-island ferry to Havelock Island (54 kms by sea from Port \r\nBlair). It takes approx 4 hrs to reach the island. Enjoy your afternoon at Beach number 7 on the western coast, better known as \"The Radha Nagar Beach\". It is one of the most popular beaches on Havelock and was named \"Best Beach in Asia\" by Time in 2004. Overnight stay at respective Hotel / Resort at Havelock Island. Hotel Symhony Palms Resort/Kingdom/T S G Resort/Holiday inn Beach Resort.','','','661492',1,'2014-12-27 11:26:59'),(566,108,'Day 03 : Havelock-Port Blair	:','Day3-120x1001419663203.jpg','This Day After Breakfast Return sail to Port Blair by  Speed Boat, O/N stay at respective Hotel / Resort at Port Blair Free for shopping in Saagarika Emporium, O/N stay in respective Hotel shompen/Is lander Inn/Classic Regency/Hotel Drift wood','','','691661',1,'2014-12-27 12:23:23'),(567,108,'Day 04 : Port Blair-Jolly Buoy/Red Skin Island-Port Blair','Day4-120x1001419664279.jpg','After breakfast, we drive to Jolly Buoy/Red Skin Island(visit only first 6 months Jolly buoy and another 6 Months Red Skin Island)\r\nJOLLYBUOY :An island in Mahatma Gandhi Marine National Park , Jolly Buoy offers a breath taking underwater view of coral and marine life. It is an ideal place for Snorkeling, Sea Bathing and Basking on the sun kissed beach. \r\nREDSKINISLAND: Red Skin Island is another island in Mahatma Gandhi Marine National Park that has a nice beach and offers spectacular view of Corals and. Evening is free for shopping.  Over night stay at respective Hotel shompen/Is lander Inn/Classic Regency/Hotel Drift wood','','','106250',1,'2014-12-27 12:41:19'),(568,108,'Day 05: Port Blair-Rose Island-North Bay-Viper Island-Port Blair','Day5-120x1001419665281.jpg','Ross	: The erstwhile capital of Port Blair during the British regime. With the ruins and also with the historical background, the   island has gained a lot of popularity among the tourist.\r\nNorth Bay	: The Coral Island with beautiful scenic view of open sea and the gate way of Andaman! Viewing of rare corals and 	   underwater marine life through glass bottom boats & Snorkeling and it&#39;s a good place for swimming. The views from the   light house of coconut plantations & the eagle&#39;s view of North Bay Island\r\nViper: (Harbour Cruise): covering Seven Ports by boats, biggest floating dry dock FDN-I, Naval  Harbour, Mainland Vessel Harbour, Back to Hotel shompen/Is lander Inn/Classic Regency/Hotel Drift wood','','','529749',1,'2014-12-27 12:58:01'),(569,108,'Day 06: Port Blair-Baratang-Port Blair','Day6-120x1001419665561.jpg','Early morning departure to Baratang holds the natures best treasures gifted to the Islands. Limestone caves, Active Mud Volcano. The Road journey from Port Blair to Baratang is through a dense jungle. Overnight stay at respective Hotel shompen/Is lander Inn/Classic Regency/Hotel Drift wood','','','930862',1,'2014-12-27 13:02:41'),(570,108,'Day 07 : Return Journey to Home','Day7-120x1001419665774.jpg','This day We will Depart to Veer Savarkar International Airport Fort For Back to Home.','','','842591',1,'2014-12-27 13:06:14'),(571,10,'DAY 01 : ARRIVE KATHMANDU ','day1-kathmandu1422815090.jpg','Arrive in Kathmandu. Upon arrival transfer to hotel, rest of the day is free to stroll around Hotel areas.</br>\r\n<b>Dinner and Overnight at Hotel in Kathmandu(3 * hotel)</b>\r\n','','','525902',1,'2015-02-01 23:54:50'),(572,10,'DAY 02 :TEMPLES SIGHTSEEING INCLUDING PASHUPATINATH TEMPLE','day2-Pashupathinath1422815181.jpg','After breakfast, enjoy sightseeing of Temple tours of Kathmandu including Pashupatinath Temple. Pashupatinath temple is one of the most significant Hindu temples of Shiva in the world,located on the banks of the Bagmati River in the eastern part of Kathmandu. It is regarded as the most sacred among the temples of Shiva (Pashupati).</br>\r\n<b>Dinner and Overnight at Hotel in Kathmandu(3 * hotel)</b>','','','157237',1,'2015-02-01 23:56:21'),(573,10,'DAY 03 :DRIVE FROM KATHMANDU TO NYALAM {3750 M} 156 KMS	','day3-Bhotekoshi River1422815251.jpg','After breakfast, proceeds to Kodari (Nepal - China Border). At our 4 hours driving, the group will enjoy with the beautiful scenery of Nepal. The Bhotekoshi River leads us up to Kodari is the second wilderness river in the world. Our boarder agent will complete custom formalities at Kodari. After Lunch; check in to the Tibetan autonomous part of China. We drive to a small Tibetan town is called Nylam.</br>\r\n<b>Overnight at Nylam Guest House</b>\r\n','','','867201',1,'2015-02-01 23:57:31'),(574,10,'DAY 04 :FULLDAY FREE AND EXCURSION TO NYALM {3750 M}','day4-tibet-entry1422815324.jpg','Full day free at Nylam for acclimatization and Nylam city excursion. It is the county seat of Nyalam County in Shigatse Prefecture It is 35 km from Zhangmu town in the same county, which is the point of entry to Nepal. Nyalam is situated at 3,750 meters (12,300 ft) above sea level.</br>\r\n<b>Overnight stay at Nylam Guest House</b>','','','959206',1,'2015-02-01 23:58:44'),(575,10,'DAY 05 :DRIVE FROM NYLAM TO NEW DONGBA {4450 M}','day5-lalung-la1422815434.jpg','Nyalam to New Dongba {4450 M} 425Kms passing through Lalung-La {5220 M} and Crossing the Brahmaputra river.</br>\r\n<b>Overnight at New Dongba Guest House</b>','','','621294',1,'2015-02-02 00:00:34'),(576,10,'DAY 06 :DRIVE FROM NEW DONGBA TO MANSAROVAR {4558 M}','day6-manassarovar1422815511.jpg','Drive to Mansarover {4558 M} 380km.Lake ManasSarovar is a personification of purity, and one who drinks water from the lake will go to the Abode of Lord Shiva after death. He is believed to be cleansed of all his sins committed over even a hundred lifetimes. According to the Hindu religion, the lake was first created in the mind of the Lord Brahma after which it manifested on Earth. Hence, in Sanskrit it is called \"Manasasarovaram\", which is a combination of the words manasa (mind) and sarovaram (lake). The lake, in Hindu religious belief, is also supposed to be the summer abode of the Hamsa goose. Considered to be sacred, the Hamsa is an important element in the symbology of the subcontinent, representing wisdom and beauty.</br>\r\n<b>Pooja, Parikrama and overnight at Guesthouse</b>','','','141900',1,'2015-02-02 00:01:51'),(577,10,'DAY 07 : POOJA&HOMA AT MANSAROVER.DRIVE TO DARCHEN (50KMS)','day7-drive to darchen1422815572.jpg','Morning, do POOJA and HOMA at Mansarover Lake. After necessary worship, drive to Darchen. \r\nDarchen is situated right in front of the sacred mountain, Mount Kailash. Its altitude is 4,575 metres (15,010 ft) and is the starting point for pilgrimages in the region.</br>\r\n<b>Overnight at Guesthouse in Darchen</b>','','','519363',1,'2015-02-02 00:02:52'),(578,10,'DAY 08 :DARCHEN TO TARBOCHE 13 KMS DRIVE & TREK TO DERAPHUK {5160 M} 7 KMS','day8-DERAPHUK1422815640.jpg','Drive from Darchen to Tarboche. This is the trek starting day for KailashParikrama. You can hire horse for the prakrima(paying approx. 2500 Yeun). You need to trek 6 to 7 hrs for this day.</br>\r\n<b>Overnight at Guesthouse at Deraphuk</b>','','','307032',1,'2015-02-02 00:04:00'),(579,10,'DAY 09 :DERAPHUK TO ZUTHULPHUK PASSING DOLMA-LA PASS {5600 M)','day9-DOLMA-LA PASS1422815697.jpg','Early morning approx. 4 AM we will start trek. Those people taking horse can start around 6 AM. This day we will trek 09/10 Hrs.</br>\r\n<b>Overnight at Guest house at Zuthulphuk</b>','','','704160',1,'2015-02-02 00:04:57'),(580,10,'DAY 10 :ZUTHULPHUK TO NEW DONGBA 415 KMS{END OF  PARIKRAMA}','day10-kailash-parikrama1422815752.jpg','This day we will trek around 3 hrs to end KailashParikrama. After prakrima, we will drive to New Dongba (05 Hrs drive).<br>\r\n<b>Overnight at Guesthouse at New Dongba</b>','','','126175',1,'2015-02-02 00:05:52'),(581,10,'DAY 11 : DRIVE TO NYALAM{425KMS} 07 Hrs DRIVE','day11-Nyali-bridge1422815807.jpg','Morning we will drive from New Dongba to Nyalm. Rest of the day is free to stroll around Nyalm.</br>\r\n<b>Overnight stay at Nylam Guest House</b>','','','408023',1,'2015-02-02 00:06:47'),(582,10,'DAY 12 :DRIVE NYALAM TO KATHMANDU {156 KMS}  06 HRS DRIVE','day12-kathmandu1422815862.jpg','Morning we will drive back to Kathmandu. Upon arrival in Kathmandu, transfer to Hotel. Rest of the day is free.<br>\r\n<b>Overnight at Hotel in Kathmandu(3 * hotel)</b>','','','991751',1,'2015-02-02 00:07:42'),(583,10,'DAY 13 :DEPARTURE TRANSFER','day13-departure1422815901.jpg','Early morning is free for your own activities. Later, timely transfer to Kathmandu International Airport in time to connect your flight to outward destination.','','','447192',1,'2015-02-02 00:08:21'),(584,8,'DAY 06 : DEPARTURE TRANSFER','day7-departure1422857234.jpg','After breakfast, free till final departure. Later timely transfer to Kathmandu International Airport to connect your flight for onward destination.','','After breakfast, free till final departure. Later timely transfer to Kathmandu International Airport to connect your flight for onward destination.','220253',1,'2015-02-02 11:37:14'),(585,114,'Day 01: Arrive Kulal Lumpur Intl Airport-Putrajaya','singapore_021424065080.jpg','On arrive at Kul intl Airport  Meet and Greet ,After Fresh up at putra Palace Proceed for Orientation tour of Purtrajaya(Federal administrative centre of Malaysia) Check in to Hotel  later  lunch at  Olive Indian Restaurant  Visit to  Petronas tower (Photo Stop Only),  War Memorial, Kings Palace, Chocolate Factory, Dinner at Delhi  Royal indian Restaurant  Overnight at  Hotel IBIS ***/Sentral pudu***/Best Western pataling Jaya*** ','','','922562',1,'2015-02-16 11:08:00'),(586,114,'Day 02: Kuala Lumpur- Batu Caves- Genting Highland','sentosa_Singapore1424065255.jpg','This This Day after Breakfast Proceed to Genting. En-route visit to Batu Caves. Later, drive to the Sky way cable car station for a relaxing, scenic ride up to Genting Highlands. To Day you have a choice to enjoy a sumptuous Indian Lunch or savour cuisines from different parts of the world. Later you can try your luck at the largest and only land-based casino in Asia -Casino-De-Genting (on your own).Dinner at Jaipur Palace Indian Restaurant, Back to Hotel Over night at Best Western  patalinga jaya***/IBIS  Hotel*** ','','','312773',1,'2015-02-16 11:10:55'),(587,114,'Day 03: Kuala lumpur- Singapore By Coach','Universal-Studios-Singapore1424065565.jpg','This Day After Breakfast  we will transferred by road to Singapore Lunch at Local Indian Restaurant in The evening Free for Leisure Optional you may shopping at Mustafa Center Or Surrounding&#39;s Overnight at Singapore  Cherry Loft***/Grand Imperial***','','','262923',1,'2015-02-16 11:16:05'),(588,114,'Day 04: City tour- Sentosa Isaland','kuala-lumpur-mandarian-hotel1424065665.jpg','This Day After Breakfast   Proceed to Half Day Guided tour of Singapore Lunch at Bay view Tandoor Indian  Restaurant in the Evening Proceed to Sentosa island (One Way Cable Car + Island Admission , SEA Aquarium, & Wings of the time ) Dinner at River Walk Tandoor Indian Restaurant, Stay at Hotel Grand Imperial***/Cherry Loft***','','','338978',1,'2015-02-16 11:17:45'),(589,114,'Day 05: Universal Studio tour','Malaysian-Attractions11424065801.jpg','This Day After Breakfast  proceed to Full Day Universal Studio with   Lunch Coupon  Step into the fantastic world of movie magic; fight villains, catch the celebrities and revel in the glamour of showbiz as you jump into the screen and \"ride the movies\" on roller coasters and other movie themed attractions. Exciting loops, sudden turns, breathtaking drops and thrilling near collisions w