 and the Kathmandu valley is the political and cultural heart of the kingdom The urban sprawl that makes up modern Kathmandu is in fact two cities, patan and Kathmandu. Meet and Greet transferred to Hotel. In the Evening Free for Leisure Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel. ','','','691407',1,'2014-09-02 11:51:30'),(57,7,'Day-02: Kathmandu','Day21409638920.jpg','This day after Breakfast  at Hotel Proceed for  sightseeing of Kathmandu to Visit Pashupatinath This is the place where holy Saddhus pray and cremations  on the Bagmati River are carried out. Also visit to Shambhunath, Bhaktpur Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel..','','','237342',1,'2014-09-02 11:52:00'),(58,7,'Day-03: Kathmandu –Manokamana Temple- Pokhara (240 kms)','day31409638949.jpg','This day after Breakfast we will transferred by road to Pokhara situated at 2,352 mtrs, its famous for good weather there are splendid views En-route you may visit to manokamana Temple (one of the Shakthi peethas) on arrive at Pokhara check in to Hotel Overnight at Hotel.','','','462872',1,'2014-09-02 11:52:29'),(59,7,'Day-04: Pokhara ','day41409638980.jpg','Early morning Sunrise trip enjoy with the View of Himalaya range of\r\nAnnapurna and Fishtail Himalaya from Sanagkot transfer at Pokhara/ B/ Fastat Hotel and start for Sightseeng tours/ ( Visit Davit fall/ Gupteshour\r\nCave/ Bindebashini temple and Seti River/ Lunch at Hotel and free for shopping / evening Boating in Fewa lake/ Evening Nepali Cultural Program show with Dinner, Overnight at Hotel','','','981451',1,'2014-09-02 11:53:00'),(60,7,'Day-5: Pokhara- Depart to you Kathmandu Airport','Day51409639010.jpg','This Morning After Breakfast we will Depart to you Kathmandu Airport  for Back to Home.','','','242500',1,'2014-09-02 11:53:30'),(61,8,'DAY 01: ARRIVE IN KATHMANDU','day1-kathmandu1422856469.jpg','Arrive at Kathmandu. Upon arrival meet, greet and assist by our office representative and transfer to Hotel. Evening explore around nearby places or Thamel area which is the major tourist hub of kathmandu.</br>\r\n<b>Overnight at Hotel in Kathmandu</b>\r\n','','','961391',1,'2014-09-02 11:56:24'),(62,8,'DAY 02: DRIVE TO POKHARA(210 KMS /05.5 HRS)','day2_pokhara1422856551.jpg','Morning, after breakfast, drive to Pokhara.\r\nPokhara&#39;s bewitching beauty has been the subject of many travel writers. Its pristine air, spectacular backdrop of snowy peaks, serene lakes and surrounding greenery make it &#39;<b><i>the jewel in the Himalaya</i></b>&#39;, a place of remarkable natural beauty. With the magnificent Annapurna range forming the backdrop and the serenity of three major lakes - Phewa, Rupa and Begnas - Pokhara is the ultimate destination for relaxation. Pokhara Valley, gateway to the Annapurna region where many a trekker finds his Shangri-la, sits high on the list of &#39;must visit&#39; places in Nepal. Rest of the day is free.</br>\r\n<b>Overnight at Hotel in Pokhara</b>','','','485981',1,'2014-09-02 11:57:03'),(63,8,'DAY 03: FLY TO JOMSOM & EXCURSION TO MUKTINATH (25 MIN FLIGHT)','day3_mukthinath_temple1422856695.jpg','Early morning after breakfast, transfer to Pokhara airport to connect your flight to Jomsom. Upon arrival at Jomsom, transfer to Muktinath by using sharing Jeep. \r\nMuktinath is a sacred place both for Hindus and Buddhists located in Muktinath Valley at an altitude of 3,710 meters at the foot of the Thorong La mountain pass (part of the Himalayas). Within Hinduism, it is called the sacred place Mukti Kshetra, which literally means the \"place of liberation ormoksha\". This temple is considered to be the 105th among the available 108 Divya Desam, which are considered sacred by the Sri Vaishnava cult. The ancient name of this place in Sri Vaishnava literature, before Buddhist origin, is <i>Thiru Saligramam</i>\r\n</br>\r\nAfter Isnan, Puja and Arati at Muktinath Temple, drive back to Jomsom.</br>\r\n<b>Overnight at Hotel in Jomsom</b>\r\n','','','415113',1,'2014-09-02 11:57:36'),(64,8,'DAY 04: FLY TO POKHARA & HALF DAY SIGHTSEEING TOUR ','day4_Bindabasini_Temple1422857038.jpg','After breakfast, fly back to Pokhara. Upon arrival, transfer to Hotel. Later commence on a half day sightseeing tour of Pokhara city including Bindabasini Temple, Seti River Gorge,  Gupteshwor Mahadev Cave and Devis Falls.</br>\r\nRest of the day is free to stroll around lake side area. \r\n</br>\r\n<b>Overnight at Hotel in Pokhara</b>\r\n','','','115665',1,'2014-09-02 11:58:43'),(65,8,'DAY 05: DRIVE BACK TO KATHMANDU VIA MANAKAMANA DARSAN','day5_cable_car_ride1422857086.jpg','Early morning after breakfast, drive back to Kathmandu. En-route visit Manakamana Devi temple. \r\nThe Manakamana Temple is situated in the Gorkha district of Nepal is the sacred place of the Hindu Goddess Bhagwati, an incarnation of Parvati. The name Manakamana originates from two words, &#34;<b><i>mana&#34;</i></b> meaning heart and &#34;<b><i>kamana&#34;</i></b> meaning wish. Venerated since the 17th century, it is believed that Goddess Bhagwati grants the wishes of all those who make the pilgrimage to her shrine to worship her.\r\nAfter darsan, continue drive back to Kathmandu and transfer to Hotel.</br>\r\n<b>Overnight at Hotel in Kathmandu</b>','','','664504',1,'2014-09-02 11:59:20'),(66,8,'DAY 06: ENJOY FULLDAY SIGHTSEEING TOUR','day6_budhanilkantha1422857199.jpg','After breakfast, commence on a full day sightseeing tour Pashupatinath Temple, Bouddhanath Stupa&#40;one of the largest Stupa&#41; and Budhanilkantha &#40;Sleeping Vishnu in water&#41;. \r\nThe Budhanilkantha statue of the Hindu god Vishnu, located approximately 10 kilometers from the center of Kathmandu at the base of the Shivapuri Hill, is the largest and most beautiful stone carving in all of Nepal. It is also the most enigmatic.\r\n<br>\r\n<b>Overnight at Hotel in Kathmandu</b>\r\n','','','659629',1,'2014-09-02 12:00:04'),(67,9,'Day 01: Arrive Colombo Intl Airport','Day11409639626.jpg','Arrive Colombo Airport, Meet and Greet Proceed to Fresh up and Breakfast at Nigambo Hotel(if Arrive Early morning Flight) proceed to Munneswaram Mahakali Temple, Thereafter visit to manaweri Temple   and then proceed to Anuradhapura First Capital of Sri Lanka in the 3 rd Century BC. Declared a World Heritage Site.,Check in at the hotel for lunch, Later Visit Sri Maha Bodhi, the oldest historically documented tree in the world, the Brazen Palace , Dagobas, Ruwanwelisaya, Abeygiri & Jetawana Monasteries, finely preserved rock-cut statues of Lord Buddha and ruins of palaces, Isurumuniya rock temple. Dinner and Overnight stay at Alakamanda/Heritage /Raja Rata Hotel – Anuradhapura.<br>\r\n<font color=\"#31336d\"><b>Muneswaram Temple, Chilaw:</b></font>\r\nAfter his victorious battle, Lord Rama left for Ayodhya, in one of King Ravana”s vimana (carriages).He felt he was being followed by bramhaasthi dosham as he had killed King Ravana who was a Brahmin. Legend has it that when he came to this place he felt bramhaasthi dosham was not following him and he stopped the vimana and asked God Shiva for remedy. Lord Shiva blessed Lord Rama and advised him to install four lingams there and pray to get rid of the dosham. Since then many Hindu devotees flock to the Temple.  \r\n<br>\r\n<font color=\"#31336d\"><b>Manaweri Temple:</b></font>\r\nManavari is the first lingam installed and prayed to by Lord Rama and this lingam is also called <b>Ramalinga Shivan</b>','','','674067',1,'2014-09-02 12:03:46'),(68,9,'Day 02: Anuradhapura-Sevenwells-Trincomalee-Dambulla','day21409639711.jpg','Breakfast at the hotel, and proceed to Trincomalee, En-route visit to Seven Wells , visit the shankaridevi Temple(Thiru Koneswaram Temple). Lunch at a restaurant (Sea Lotus Park Hotel) Evening visit the Dambulla Temple,Dinner and overnight stay at  Eden Garden/pelwehera Village  Hotel – Dambulla.\r\nThiru Koneshwaram (Shankari Devi Temple):\r\nThiru Koneshwaram was built by sage Agasthyar as per the instructions of Lord Shiva who was \r\nimpressed by the devotion of King Ravana. This place has the uniqueness of the lord building a temple for his devotee as a reward for his devotion. Lord Rama also offered his prayers on his return to get himself rid of the Brahmaasthi Dosham\r\n','','','582347',1,'2014-09-02 12:05:11'),(69,9,'Day 03: Dambulla-Kandy-Pinnawala- Ramboda-Nuwala Eliaya.','day31409639751.JPG','Breakfast at the hotel; proceed to Kandy,  visit to Kandy Tooth relic temple, Walk  surrounding Kandy lake  lunch at a restaurant,\r\nThereafter proceed to Ramboda(Sri Bhaktha Hanuman Temple)\r\nDinner and overnight stay at Anish Park /Alpine Hotel – Nuwara Eliya.\r\nSri Baktha Hanuman Temple, Ramboda :\r\nOn these hills of Ramboda where Hanuman was searching for Sitadevi, the Chinmaya mission of Sri Lanka built a temple with Hanuman as the presiding deity. On every full moon day special pooja”s are conducted and witnessed by thousands of devotees.\r\n','','','729242',1,'2014-09-02 12:05:51'),(70,9,'Day 04: Nuwara Eliya -Sita Eliaya- Ashokavatika-Hakagala-Divurompala-Ravan Velawaya-Banderwala.','day41409639885.jpg','Breakfast at the hotel, and proceed to Sita Eliya(Sita Amman Temple),Ashokvatika, Hakagala Botanical Garden  Lunch at Ella Hotel Later visit  to  Ravana Ella & Ravana Caves,Dinner and overnight stay at Bandarawela Hotel – Banadarawela.\r\nSeetha Amman Temple, Seetha Eliya: \r\nThe stream that runs from the hill, catered to the needs of Sitadevi during her stay at Ashoka Vatika. She is said to have bathed in this stream. Now there is a temple erected for Lord Rama, Sitadevi, Luxshmana and Hanuman by the side of this stream. It is interesting to note that footprints akin to Lord Hamunams are found by this river -some small and some large.\r\nThe Hakgala Botanical Garden:\r\n was one of the pleasure gardens of King Ravana of the well-known epic Ramayana. This garden was expanded during the British period and has a wide variety of flowers including an excellent collection of orchids.This is the exotic pleasure garden where king Ravana kept the depressed Sita, insisting that she marry him. It was here where the heart-warming meeting took place between her and Hanuman, who brought \r\nher Rama’s ring with the news that Rama was looking for her. He offered to carry her back but she refused saying it would be an insult to Rama’s honour if he did so.  Divurumpola:\r\nSita met Rama after the war, and Divurumpola is the place she under went the \"Agni\" test of fire where she proved her innocence and purity to Rama. Divurumpola means the \"Place of Oath\" in Sinhala. She came out unscathed and proved her innocence and purity.','','','677750',1,'2014-09-02 12:08:05'),(71,9,'Day 05: Banderwala-Colombo','day51409639913.jpg','Breakfast at the hotel, and proceed to Colombo, Lunch at Belihuloya Restaurant, at ColomboLater do a city tour of Colombo  Visit Fort, the former British administrative centre and military garrison, Sea Street - the Goldsmith&#39;s quarters in the heart of Pettah, the Bazaar area, where there is a Hindu Temple with elaborate stone carvings, and the Dutch Church of Wolfendhal dating back to 1749. The historic Dawatagaha Mosque and the former Eye Hospital are two buildings in Cinnamon Gardens worth looking at. Also visit the BMICH, see the replica of Avukana Buddha and the Independence Square.Dinner and overnight stay at Berjaya Mount Royal – Mount Lavinia.\r\n','','','157044',1,'2014-09-02 12:08:33'),(72,9,'Day 06: Depart to Colombo Airport','day61409639947.jpg','Breakfast at the hotel, and proceed to the airport for departure.\r\n<br> \r\nEnd of Tour.\r\n','','','679156',1,'2014-09-02 12:09:07'),(73,17,'Day 1 : Arrive Manali','day11410327331.jpg','Arrive  Manali a picture-perfect hill resort at an altitude of 1,929 metres. Set amidst pine-clad mountains, which gradually close in on both sides of the Beas and nestling in their shade, as though carved out of primeval forest, is a scattered hamlet, which comprises this picturesque summer resort. Proceed to your hotel. Rest of the evening is at leisure, overnight at the hotel','','','456509',1,'2014-09-10 11:05:31'),(74,17,'Day 2 	:	 Manali','day21410327370.jpg','This morning you will visit the Solang Valley, which offers fine views of glaciers and snow, capped peaks. A place not to be missed is Rohtang Pass, 51 km from Manali at an altitude of 3978 meters (subject to weather conditions). Also visit to Hadimba Temple, Vashist Kund, Nagar Castle In the Evening Free for Leisure Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel.','','','999116',1,'2014-09-10 11:06:10'),(75,17,'Day 3 : Depart to Manali','day31410327512.jpg','This day after breakfast we will Depart to you Manali Bus Station for Back to Home.\r\n','','','479278',1,'2014-09-10 11:08:32'),(76,0,'','','','','','',1,'2014-09-10 11:21:53'),(77,0,'','','','','','',1,'2014-09-10 11:23:38'),(78,0,'','','','','','',1,'2014-09-10 11:36:53'),(79,0,'','','','','','',1,'2014-09-10 23:01:12'),(80,16,'Day 01 : Ramoji Filmcity tour','RFC_Day11410646218.jpg','07:00 Am: Chandanagar\r\n07:30 Am: Kukatpally\r\n08:00 Am : Hi-Tech City Cyber Tower\r\n08:30 Am: Lakidaka pool\r\nOnward Journey  to Ramoji Film City\r\n','','','438209',1,'2014-09-14 03:40:18'),(81,12,'Day 1	: 	Arrive Srinagar ','Day11410646597.jpg','Arrive Srinagar, a Lake city of Kashmir, located in the heart of the Kashmir valley at an altitude of 1,730 m above sea level, famous for its lakes dotted with Shikaras,  and the Mughal Gardens.. Transfer to hotel. This afternoon visit the world famous Mughal gardens built by Emperor Jehangir. Enjoy a ‘Shikara ride’ on the picturesque Dal lake. Overnight on board House Boat/hotel','','','903492',1,'2014-09-14 03:46:37'),(82,12,'Day 2 	:	 Srinagar – Gulmarg – Srinagar (56 kms / 2 hrs one way)','Day21410646680.jpg','This morning proceed for a full day excursion to Gulmarg, a Meadow of Flowers situated at an altitude of 2730 meters, and a famous ski resort during the winters. Enjoy leisurely walks on the lush green meadows of flowers with a backdrop of the snow capped mountains OR enjoy an optional Gondola ride (Cable Car). Overnight on board the  House Boat/Hotel.','','','749729',1,'2014-09-14 03:48:00'),(83,12,'Day 3 	:	 Srinagar – Sonemarg – Srinagar (85 kms/3-4 hrs one way)','Day31410646722.jpg','Drive to Sonamarg through the Sindh Valley which presents yet another spectacular facet of countryside in Kashmir. Situated at an altitude of 2730 m, Sonamarg (&#39;The meadow of gold&#39;) has, as its backdrop, snowy mountains against a cerulean sky. Optionally visit Thajiwas glacier, a major local attraction during the summer months. Evening drive back to Srinagar. Overnight on board the Houseboat/Hotel','','','573000',1,'2014-09-14 03:48:42'),(84,12,'Day 4 	:	 Srinagar – Pahalgam (94 kms/3 -4  hrs)','Day41410646785.jpg','Today you will be transferred by road to Pahalgam, the Valley of Shepherds - Situated at the confluence of the streams flowing from Sheshnag Lake and the Lidder river, situated at 2,130 m.  Arrive and proceed to your hotel, rest of the day at leisure to explore the countryside  on your own. Overnight at the hotel','','','215182',1,'2014-09-14 03:49:45'),(85,12,'Day 5 	:	 Pahalgam -  Srinagar','Day51410646830.jpg','This morning is at leisure. Later you will be transferred back to Srinagar, rest of the day at leisure for shopping and own activities, overnight on board the Houseboat/Hotel.','','','552085',1,'2014-09-14 03:50:30'),(86,12,'Day 6 	:	 Depart Srinagar','Day61410646862.jpg','Transfer to airport for your onward flight back home','','','525749',1,'2014-09-14 03:51:02'),(87,13,'Day 1: Arrive Gangtok (90 kms / 2-3 hrs)','Day11410647020.jpg','Arrive This morning you will be transferred by road to Gangtok, is literally the “lofty hill” set amidst the clouds and mists of the splendorous Himalayas and is a gateway to Sikkim.Proceed to your hotel and rest\r\nof the day at leisure. Overnight at the hotel.\r\n','','','795315',1,'2014-09-14 03:53:40'),(88,13,'Day 2 :  Gangtok','Day21410647115.JPG','This morning proceed on an excursion to Baba Mandir, dedicated to a old soldier of Indian Army, later visit picturesque Tsomgo lake, a holy lake worshipped by the Sikkimese. Enjoy an optional yak ride around the lake. Overnight at hotel.','','','914777',1,'2014-09-14 03:55:15'),(89,13,'Day 3 :  Gangtok-Pelling(120 km/4-5 hrs)','Day31410647236.jpg','Today you will be transferred to Pelling. A placid Pelling pulls most of the visitors for its representative status in history, nature and culture of the state. Situated at an altitude of 6,800 ft, famous for its magnificent view of the snow-capped mountains of Khangchendzonga. Arrive and proceed to your hotel, Later Afternoon you will visit Pemayangtse monastery, situated on the back drop of the Eastern Himalayas, built in 17th Century AD, which houses several religious images and other objects of worship, most of which are precious because of their ancientness. Later you will visit tranquil Khecheopalri Lake, surrounded by blooming forest and is considered as one of the sacred lakes of Sikkim both by the Buddhist and the Hindus. Back to Hotel Overnight at Pelling Hotel.\r\n','','','444832',1,'2014-09-14 03:57:16'),(90,13,'Day 4 :  Pelling- Darjeeling','Day41410647298.jpg','This day after Breakfast we will transfer to Darjeeling. Enroute you will visit beautiful Mirik Lake. Arrive and proceed to your hotel. Overnight at thehotel.','','','431091',1,'2014-09-14 03:58:18'),(91,13,'Day 5 :  Darjeeling ','Day51410647350.jpg','Early morning (0330 hrs) visit Tiger Hills to witness the spectacular sunrise over the Kanchanjunga mountains. On the return visit the famous Ghoom Monastery and Batasia loop. This afternoon visit the Himalayan Mountaineering Institute, the Himalayan Zoo and the Botanical Gardens. At the end of the tour visit the Tibetan Handicraft Center and drive past Darjeeling Tea Gardens. Overnight at hotel.','','','266015',1,'2014-09-14 03:59:10'),(92,13,'Day 6 :  Depart Baghdogra (124 kms / 4 – 5 hrs)','Day61410647412.jpg','This day After Breakfast we will Depart to Baghdogra Airport/Rly stn En-route you may visit to Buitiful Merik Lake, Pashupathinagar.','','','166863',1,'2014-09-14 04:00:12'),(93,14,'Day 01 : Arrive Cochin-Munnar','Day11410647626.jpg','On arrive at Trichur Rly stn Meet and\r\nGreet Proceed to Munnar, a picture book towns and winding lanes, Munnar\r\nis one of the most exotic of hill stations of Kerala. Rest of the day is at leisure.\r\nOvernight at hotel.\r\n','','','553184',1,'2014-09-14 04:03:46'),(94,95,'Day 01 : Pune - Mahabaleshwar ( 120 km /4-5 hrs)','Day11410648008.jpg','Arrival at Pune meet and greet transferred to you Mahablaeshwer The Birth Place of Holy Rivers Savithri,Gayatri,Koyana,Venna,Krishna.En-route visit to Panchgani,   check in your hotel rest of the evening Optional you may visit to Venna Lake The Birth Place of Venna River Back to Hotel over night at hotel. ','','','382196',1,'2014-09-14 04:10:08'),(95,95,'Day 02 : Mahabaleshwar ','Day21410648074.jpg','Today morning, after breakfast you will visit this beautiful hill station. It has pleasant walks & good lookouts, and the area has interesting historical connections with Shivaji Prathap Garh, Tapola Lake  the Back water of koyana Dam  Optional take boat ride,  Panchgani Temple, Shanker ji Temple, Krishna bai temple you may see Starting  Point of Krishna River from this temple, Arthur seat (its called as 12 Points), Kates point, you may see Heliphant Head from Needle’s Hole Point Back to Hotel Over Night at Hotel','','','326691',1,'2014-09-14 04:11:14'),(96,95,'Day 03: Mahabaleshwar - Lonavala ( 180 km/4-5 hrs)','Day31410648162.jpg','This day after breakfast we will transferred you to by road Lonavala The Resort city of Maharashtra Arrive and Check in Hotel Over night at Hotel','','','217151',1,'2014-09-14 04:12:42'),(97,95,'Day 04: Lonavala','Day41410648221.jpg','To Day after breakfast you will  proceed to sightseeing of Lonavala – Khandala , Karla and Bhaja Caves, Filmy Shooting Point explore the beautiful surroundings. Rest of the evening  walking on the surrounding lush greens Overnight at hotel. ','','','655262',1,'2014-09-14 04:13:41'),(98,95,'Day 05: Lonavala- Pune','Day51410648328.jpg','Today after breakfast we will depart you to Pune Airport Or Rly  Stn for Back to Home with  Unlimited sweet Memories','','','605553',1,'2014-09-14 04:15:28'),(99,17,'Day 1 : Arrive Manali','day11410702703.jpg','Arrive  Manali a picture-perfect hill resort at an altitude of 1,929 metres. Set amidst pine-clad mountains, which gradually close in on both sides of the Beas and nestling in their shade, as though carved out of primeval forest, is a scattered hamlet, which comprises this picturesque summer resort. Proceed to your hotel. Rest of the evening is at leisure, overnight at the hotel.','','','507339',0,'2014-09-14 19:21:43'),(100,0,'','','','','','',1,'2014-09-14 19:38:28'),(101,18,'Day 1: Arrive Jaipur','day11410703907.jpg','This Day you will  Arrive Jaipur. Transfer to your hotel. After Breakfast  you will tour the city of Jaipur visit the City Palace, an overwhelming complex of exquisite palaces, gardens and courtyards. Visit the palace museum that houses collections of rare manuscripts, armory, Costumes, carpets and miniature paintings. Walk to the adjacent Jantarmantar an astronomical observatory built in 17th century. Lastly you will drive past the Hawa Mahal, a Palace of winds. Also visit to  Amer fort an ancient capital of Jaipur, you will see magnificent palaces with walls covered with mirrored mosaics. Enjoy an elephant ride at the Amer fort. Rest of the day is at leisure for shopping and own activities, overnight at the hotel.','','','955581',1,'2014-09-14 19:41:47'),(102,18,'Day2 : Jaipur-Ajmer-Pushker-Jaipur  (120  kms/2 –3 hrs/ One Way)','day21410703959.jpg','This Day After Breakfast you will Proceed  to visit the holy towns of Pushkar & Ajmer. Visit the Pushkar Lake & a Brahma temple in Pushkar, while in Ajmer visit the Dargah of Salim Chisti. Back to Jaipur Overnight at Jaipur\r\n','','','792687',1,'2014-09-14 19:42:39'),(103,18,'Day3 : Depart to Jaipur','day31410704003.jpg','This Day After Breakfast you will be free for Leisure Optional you may be  Explore to Jaipur On your Own / Shopping  in the Evening we will Depart to Jodhpur Bus station\r\n','','','420108',1,'2014-09-14 19:43:23'),(104,19,'Day 01	: Arrive 	Haridwar ','Day11410704120.jpeg','On arrive at   Haridwar, on the right bank of River Ganga at the feet of Shivalik ranges, an ancient pilgrim city is one of the holiest places for Hindus. Arrive and proceed to your hotel. Later Afternoon visit to Manasa Devi Temple , Naina Devi Temple in the  evening you will visit the famous ghat of Hari ki Paudi to witness an evening Ganga Aarti ceremony, overnight at the hotel','','','331556',1,'2014-09-14 19:45:20'),(105,19,'Day 02	:	Haridwar – Rishikesh-Haridwar','day21410704158.jpg','Early this morning you will visit to  Rishikesh  Ramjula and Laxamjul, Sivanand Ashramam, Swarg Ashramam and Geetha Ashramam in the Evening we will Depart to Haridwar Bus Bay for Back to Delhi.\r\n','','','923929',1,'2014-09-14 19:45:58'),(106,20,'Day 1  :  Arrive Katra','day11410704213.jpg','On arrive at  Katra, A Base City of Maa Viashnodevi Temple Cehck in to Hotel After Fresh up Start trekking/By Pouni/By Heli  to Pooja and Dharshan Maa Vashnodevi Temple Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel.\r\n','','','313596',1,'2014-09-14 19:46:53'),(107,20,'Day 2  :  Katra- Patnitop','day21410704269.jpg','This Day after Breakfast we will Transferred to Patnitop perched on a beautiful plateau, at an altitude of 2024 m, Enveloped by thickly wooded forests Proceed to your hotel Later Afternoon Visiting The Shudh Maha Devi ka Pahad That Houses The Holy Trishul (Trident). Overnight at Patnitop Hotel\r\n','','','491989',1,'2014-09-14 19:47:49'),(108,20,'Day 3   :  Patnitop - Deaprt Katra','day31410704301.jpg','This Day After Breakfast you will be Free for Leisure in the Evening we will Depart Katra for Back to Delhi\r\n','','','421110',1,'2014-09-14 19:48:21'),(109,21,'Day 1 	:	 Delhi – Agra  (206 kms/3-4 hrs)','day11410704377.jpg','Today you will drive to Mughal city Agra. Arrive and check into your hotel. This afternoon visit the Agra fort, Built by the great Emperor Akbar, proceed to the Taj Mahal, built by Emperor Shah Jahan in memory of his wife Mumtaz Mahal. This evening is at leisure for shopping and individual activities.  Overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','447661',1,'2014-09-14 19:49:37'),(110,21,'Day 2 	:	 Agra – Fatehpursikri-Mathura-Delhi (236 kms/5 – 6  hrs)','day21410704415.jpg','This Morning visit  Fatehpur Sikri, the deserted red sandstone city built by the  Mughal Emperor Akbar. Also visit to Mathura Temple( The Birth Place of Lord Krishna) later  you will Be Back Delhi.\r\n','','','256016',1,'2014-09-14 19:50:15'),(111,22,'Day 1: Arrive  Udaipur ','day11410704746.jpg','Arrive Udaipur Meet and Greet Transferred to Hotel After Fresh up  Proceed for  sightseeing tour of Udaipur visit to the City palace  and museum, proceed to Jagdish temple and lastly visit the Sahelion Ki Bari “Gardens of the Maidens”. In the evening you will be Free for leisure Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel.\r\n','','','728630',1,'2014-09-14 19:55:46'),(112,22,'Day2 : Jodhpur-Mount Abu(275 km/4-5 Hrs)','day21410704789.jpg','This day After Breakfast we will transfer by road to Mount Abu, the Only Hill Station in Rajasthan at an Altitude of 1,220mts. crowning the highest peak of the Aravali Hills .On arrive Mount Abu check in to Hotel Later Afternoon you will  visit the magnificent Dilwara Jain Temples built in 11th century, sunset point, Nakki Lake. In the Evening Free for Leisure Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel.\r\n','','','177637',1,'2014-09-14 19:56:29'),(113,22,'Day3 : Depart to Udaipur','day31410704827.jpg','This Day After Breakfast we will  Depart to Udaipur for Back to Delhi.\r\n','','','586303',1,'2014-09-14 19:57:07'),(114,23,'Day 1 	:	Dharamshala','Day11410705353.jpg','O