-14 23:11:09'),(138,34,'Day 01 :Hyderabad-Shiridi','Day1_at_Shirdi_Saibab1410716653.jpg','This Day Evening Start by Volvo/Hi-tech Bus for Onward Journey to Holy town  of  Saibaba Temple Overnight at Bus\r\n','','','687895',1,'2014-09-14 23:13:33'),(139,34,'Day 02 :Arrive Shiridi','Day2_at_Shanisinghnapur1410716701.jpg','Arrive  Shiridi the Holy pilgrimage of Holy Sai Baba Temple Arrive Check in to Hotel After Fresh up Proceed for Pooja and Dharshan of Lord Sai Baba Later you will proceed for Pooja and Dhrshan of  Lord Shani at Shanisinghnapur Back to Shiridi Overnight at Shirdi.\r\n','','','213210',1,'2014-09-14 23:15:01'),(140,34,'Day 03 :Shiridi-Nasik-Trimbakeshwar-Depart to Shiridi','Day3_at_trimbakeshwar1410716737.jpg','After Breakfast Proceed to Sightseeing of Nashik City Covering Places-Coin Musem, Kalaram Mandir,Pandu Lena,Ramkund,MuktidhamTemple,Someshwar Later Visit to Trimbakeshwar( one of the 12 jyothirlingas) .Back to Shiridi Depart to Shirdi Back to Home By Coach.\r\n','','','744100',1,'2014-09-14 23:15:37'),(141,34,'Day 04 :Hyderabad','Day41410716770.jpg','This Day Early Morning you will be at Hyderabad\r\n','','','398568',1,'2014-09-14 23:16:10'),(142,35,'Day 01 : Pune - Mahabaleshwar ( 120 km /4-5 hrs)','Day1_at_Mahabaleshwar1410716825.jpg','Arrival at Pune meet and greet transferred to you Mahablaeshwer The Birth Place of Holy Rivers Savithri,Gayatri,Koyana,Venna,Krishna   check in your hotel Later Afternoon Proceed for Sightseeing of Venna lake, Elephant Head,Shankar ji Temple, Krishna Bai Temple, Also visit to Famous Arthur Seat Point and lastly visit to Sunset Point Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel.\r\n','','','544623',1,'2014-09-14 23:17:05'),(143,35,'Day 02 : Mahabaleshwar ','Day2_boating_at_tapola1410716865.jpg','Today morning, after breakfast you will visit this beautiful hill station. It has pleasant walks & good lookouts, and the area has interesting historical connections with Shivaji Prathap Garh. Afternoon you have an opportunity to go to Tapola Lake The Back Water of Koyana Dam Optional take Boat Ride in the Evening Free for Leisure Overnight at Mahabaleshwar Hotel. \r\n','','','536105',1,'2014-09-14 23:17:45'),(144,35,'Day 03: Mahablaeshwar – Depart to Pune ','Day3_Departure1410716893.JPG','This Day After Breakfast  we will Depart to Pune Bus Station for Back to Home.\r\n','','','395070',1,'2014-09-14 23:18:13'),(145,36,'Day 1- Pune-Morgaon- Siddhatek-Siddhatek-Pune','Day11410716952.jpg','On arrive to Pune Check in to hotel, After Fresh up  Drive to Morgaon (Mayuresshwer/66 Km/1-2)  after darshan leave for Siddhatek(Siddha Vinayak/70 Km/1-2 Hrs). On arrival take darshan and then halt for lunch. After lunch leave for Theur(Chintamani/89 Km/1-2 Hrs)  Back to Pune Overnight at Pune.\r\n','','','538166',1,'2014-09-14 23:19:12'),(146,36,'Day 2- Pune –Ranjangoan--Ozhar-Lenvandri-Pune','Day21410716980.jpg','This Morning Drive to Ranjangaon(Mahaganapathi/52 Km/1-2 Hrs) After Dardhan Proceed to Ozar(Vighneshwar/90 Km/2-3 Hrs) Halt for Lunch, Then Drive to Lenyandri(Girijatmaj/90 Km/2-3 Hrs) While Back to Pune Visit to Bhimshanker Temple( One of The 12 Jyothirlingam) Back to Pune Overnight  at Pune\r\n','','','785624',1,'2014-09-14 23:19:40'),(147,36,'Day 3- Mahad-Pali-Pune','day31410717009.jpg','This Day After Breakfast Proceed to Mahad(Varad Vinayak/131 Km/2-3 Hrs) After Darshan and Pooja Proceed  Pali(Balaleshwar/70 Km/1-2 Hrs)-in The Evening we will Depart to Pune(120 Km/2-3 Hrs) Bus Station  for Back to Home.\r\n','','','446540',1,'2014-09-14 23:20:09'),(148,37,'Day 1- Pune-Morgaon-Siddhatek-Pune','Day11410717062.jpg','On arrive to Pune Check in to hotel, After Fresh up  Drive to Morgaon (Mayuresshwer/66 Km/1-2)  after darshan leave for Siddhatek(Siddha Vinayak/70 Km/1-2 Hrs). On arrival take darshan and then halt for lunch. After lunch leave for Theur(Chintamani/89 Km/1-2 Hrs)  Back to Pune Overnight at Pune\r\n','','','355088',1,'2014-09-14 23:21:02'),(149,37,'Day 2- Pune –Ranjangoan--Ozhar-Lenvandri-Bhimshanker-Pune','Day21410717098.JPG','This Morning Drive to Ranjangaon(Mahaganapathi/52 Km/1-2 Hrs) After Dardhan Proceed to Ozar(Vighneshwar/90 Km/2-3 Hrs) Halt for Lunch, Then Drive to Lenyandri(Girijatmaj/90 Km/2-3 Hrs) While Back to Pune Visit to Bhimshanker Temple( One of The 12 Jyothirlingam) Back to Pune Overnight  at Pune\r\n','','','421131',1,'2014-09-14 23:21:38'),(150,37,'Day 3- Pune-Mahad-Pali-Kolhapur','Day31410717126.jpg','This Day After Breakfast Proceed to Mahad(Varad Vinayak/131 Km/2-3 Hrs) After Darshan and Pooja Proceed  Pali(Balaleshwar/70 Km/1-2 Hrs)-in Later we will Transferred by road to  Kolhapur Arrive Kolhapur Overnight at Hotel.\r\n','','','130509',1,'2014-09-14 23:22:06'),(151,37,'Day 4- Kolhapur-Laxmi Devi Temple- Depart to Kolhapur Rly stn','Day41410717162.jpg','This Day Early Hours you will Proceed to Pooja and Dharsahn of Sree Mahalaxmi Temple Back to Hotel After Breakfast we will Depart to Kolhapur Bus  stn for Back to Home.\r\n','','','567269',1,'2014-09-14 23:22:42'),(152,38,'Day 01 : Aurangabad - Ajanta ','Day11410717208.jpg','On arrival Aurangabad check in into hotel. After Fresh up   proceed for excursion of 105 kms – 2hrs to witness famous Ajanta caves. Ajanta is one of the few historical and architectural marvels of India. Recognized as the World Heritage site today, it was discovered during the 19th century by a group of British officers who were on a tiger hunt. The Ajanta group of caves, located deep within the Sahyadri hills above the Waghora, depicts the story of Buddhism that prevailed here during 200 BC to 650 AD. After visiting Ajanta Caves drive back to Aurangabad. Return to Aurangabad for overnight\r\n','','','576098',1,'2014-09-14 23:23:28'),(153,38,'Day 02 : Aurangabad – Ellora-Grishmeshwara Temple','Day2_Grishneshwar1410717240.jpg','After breakfast take a sight seeing tour of Ellora – 30 kms, ½ hours, one of the highly visited World heritage sites of India. It houses 34 monasteries and temples with some exclusive uninterrupted sequence of monuments that date back from 600 to 1000 AD. The temples of Ellora is dedicated to Brahmanism, Jainism, and Buddhism. It also has some of the excellent stonework depicting the legends related to Lord Shiva. Also visit to Grishneshwar Temple(one of the 12 Jyothirlingas).In The Evening we will Depart to Aurangabad Bus Station  for Back to Home.\r\n','','','398071',1,'2014-09-14 23:24:00'),(154,39,'Day 01	: Madurai (142 kms/3-4 hrs)','Day1_at_Rameshwaram1410717309.jpg','On arrive at  Madurai, Southern India&#39;s oldest city with a recorded history going back to the 6th century B.C. This afternoon you will visit the ruins of the Tirumal Nayak Palace and world famous Meenakshi Temple, the most perfect example of Dravidian architecture. Later this evening you may revisit the Temple for the evening Aarti ceremony. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','802543',1,'2014-09-14 23:25:09'),(155,39,'Day 02	:	Madurai-Rameshwaram(160 Km/3-4 Hrs)','Day2_at_Thirumal-Nayak1410717379.jpg','This day After Breakfast Proceed to Rameshwarm in Tamil Nadu is popularly referred to as &#39;Benaras of the South.&#39; Rameshwaram happens to be one of the most visited pilgrim sites of India. Legend has it that to attain Moksha, a visit to Rameshwaram is mandatory. In the epic Ramayana, there is mention of Rameshwaram at various places. Rameshwaram is at a distance of just 24 kms from Sri Lanka. Spread over an area of 61.8 square kilometres, Rameshwaram happens to be in the shape of a conch. On arrival at Rameshwaram visit to Ramanthawamy Temple,Kodandaramaswamy temple, Sethu Five km south of the temple is Sethu, where the celebrated temple of Sri Anjaneya is situated, and where, it is believed, Sri Rama built a bridge to Sri Lanka .Overnight at Hotel.\r\n','','','881852',1,'2014-09-14 23:26:19'),(156,39,'Day 03	:	Depart to Madurai','Day31410717402.jpg','This Day After Breakfast we will Depart to Madurai for Back to Home.\r\n','','','508356',1,'2014-09-14 23:26:42'),(157,40,'Day 01	:	Madurai – Tanjore – Trichy  (150 kms/3-4 hs)','Day1_at_Big-temple-thanjavur1410717448.jpg','On arrive at Madurai Airport/Rly stn  Meet and Greet Proceed  by road Trichy,  en-route visiting world famous Brihadeshwara Temple at Tanjore. This afternoon you will visit the famous Rock Fort, which is a landmark of Trichy lastly visit     Srirangam  Island, a living example of the ancient temple towns of the south. Overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','984218',1,'2014-09-14 23:27:28'),(158,40,'Day 02	:	Trichy – Madurai (142 kms/3-4 hrs)','Day2_at_thirumalai-nayak-mahal1410717474.jpg','This morning you will drive to Madurai, Southern India&#39;s oldest city with a recorded history going back to the 6th century B.C. This afternoon you will visit the ruins of the Tirumal Nayak Palace and world famous Meenakshi Temple, the most perfect example of Dravidian architecture. Later this evening you may revisit the Temple for the evening Aarti ceremony. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','696827',1,'2014-09-14 23:27:54'),(159,40,'Day 03	:	Madurai-Rameshwaram-Madurai( 160 Km/Each way/4-5 Hrs)','Day3_at_sethu1410717514.jpg','This day After Breakfast Proceed to Rameshwarm in Tamil Nadu is popularly referred to as &#39;Benaras of the South.&#39; Rameshwaram happens to be one of the most visited pilgrim sites of India. Legend has it that to attain Moksha, a visit to Rameshwaram is mandatory. In the epic Ramayana, there is mention of Rameshwaram at various places. Rameshwaram is at a distance of just 24 kms from Sri Lanka. Spread over an area of 61.8 square kilometres, Rameshwaram happens to be in the shape of a conch.On arrival at Rameshwaram visit to Ramanthawamy Temple,Kodandaramaswamy temple, Sethu Five km south of the temple is Sethu, where the celebrated temple of Sri Anjaneya is situated, and where, it is believed, Sri Rama built a bridge to Sri Lanka.Back to Madurai Overnight at Madurai.\r\n','','','881576',1,'2014-09-14 23:28:34'),(160,40,'Day 04	: Depart to Madurai','Thubnail1410717556.jpg','This Day we will Depart to Madurai Airport/Rly stn for Back to Home.\r\n','','','475509',1,'2014-09-14 23:29:16'),(161,41,'Day 01	:	Cochin-Munnar','Day1_at_misty-munnar1410717616.jpg','On arrive Cochin Meet and Greet Transferred to Munnar, a picture book towns and winding lanes, Munnar is one of the most exotic of hill stations of Kerala. Rest of the day is at leisure.Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','978233',1,'2014-09-14 23:30:16'),(162,41,'Day 02	:	Munnar','Day2_at_Muttupetty-dam1410717644.jpg','This morning you will proceed on a sightseeing tour of the picturesque Munnar, visit Raja Malai, a top peak of Munnar where you can see Neel Thar (mountain goats), Muttupetty dam. Continue your tour to Echo Point. Rest of the day is at leisure, overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','477818',1,'2014-09-14 23:30:44'),(163,41,'Day 03	:Thekkady-Allepphy - Kettuvalam(House Boat)(130kms/3-4hrs)','Day3_atkettuvallam-houseboat-011410717670.jpg','Today you will board a Kettuvalam the famous Houseboats of Kerala. Cruise through the unique web of lakes, lagoons, canals, rivers and India’s most enchanting areas - a rural, riverine expanse of verdant coconut groves and rice paddies. Overnight onboard Houseboat.\r\n','','','625246',1,'2014-09-14 23:31:10'),(164,41,'Day 04	:	Allepphy-Depart to Cochin (30 Kms / 1-2 Hrs )','Day4_at_paddies1410717697.jpg','This Day  we will Depart to Cochin for Back to Home \r\n','','','613479',1,'2014-09-14 23:31:37'),(165,42,'Day 01	:	Chennai – Mahabalipuram – Kanchipuram (65 kms/1-2 hrs)','Day11410717760.jpg','Meet and Greet  proceed on an excursion to famous Shore Temples of Mahabalipuram, most outstanding examples of Dravidian art and architecture later visit famous Kailashnatha temple at Kanchipuram, overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','740248',1,'2014-09-14 23:32:40'),(166,42,'Day 02	:	Kanchipuram– Pondicherry (132 kms/3-4 hrs)','Day21410717786.jpg','Today you will drive to Pondicherry, capital of the French colonies in India since the 17th century. This afternoon visit Arobindo Ashram, a seat of learning and Vedic cultures since ancient times, proceed to Church of the Sacred Heart of Jesus, noted for its Gothic architecture and stained glass panels, lastly you will visit Auroville, planned city of Dawn of the new world. Overnight at the hotel. \r\n','','','532750',1,'2014-09-14 23:33:06'),(167,42,'Day 03	:	Pondicherry – Depart to Chennai','Day31410717814.jpg','Afternoon proceed on a sightseeing tour of the city visiting the Kapaleshwar Temple, Fort St. George and the Government Museum. The rest of the evening is at leisure OR optionally you may visit &#39;Dakshinchitra&#39;. In the Evening we will Depart to Chennai for Back to Home.\r\n','','','514079',1,'2014-09-14 23:33:34'),(168,43,'Day 01: Arrive Manglore(360 Km/7-8 Hrs)','Day1_at_water-sports1410717868.jpg','Arrive Manglore  Check  in to Hotel Later Afternoon visit to Sultan Battery, Kadri Manjunath Temple,Mangala Devi Temple, Gokarnatheshwara Temple,Tannirbhavi Beach Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel.\r\n','','','166209',1,'2014-09-14 23:34:28'),(169,43,'Day 02 :	Mangalore –Annpoorneshwari Temple(125 Km/2-3 Hrs)-Kalaseshwara Temple-Sharadamba Temple(45','day2_at_Sharadamba_temple1410717914.jpeg','This After Breakfast you will Proceed to Udipi En-route visit to Annapoorneshwari Temple at Horanadu, Kalasa: Kalaseshwara Temple, Sharadhamba Temple at Singeri, Kudhermukh National Park.Arrive Udipi Check in to Hotel In the Evening Free for Leisure Optional you will visit to Krishna Mutt,Kaup Beach Back to Hotel Over night at Hotel. \r\n','','','835581',1,'2014-09-14 23:35:14'),(170,43,'Day 03 : Udipi- Mookambika Temple(70 Km/1-2 Hrs)-Murdeshwara Temple(59 Km/1-1 Hr)-Gokarna(70 Km/1-','Day3_At_Gokarna1410717947.jpg','This Morning you will Proceed to Gokarna The Holy City of Hindu Religious, En-route you visit to Mookambika Temple, Murdeshwara Temple The  Second Largest Shiva Statue, Arrive Gokaran Visit to Mahabaleshwara Temple, Bhadrakali Temple,Ganapathi Temple In the Evening Free for Leisure Opational you may Walk Through Om Beach Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel.  \r\n','','','135471',1,'2014-09-14 23:35:47'),(171,43,'Day 04	:	Gokaran-Jogfalls -Depart to Udupi  Bus Station','Day4_AT_jog-falls1410717988.jpg','This Day After Breakfast we will Depart to Udipi Bus station For Back to Home .En-route visit to  Jogfalls, Tallest Waterfalls in India situated at Western Ghats. In the Evening we will Depart  Udupi  Bus Station for Back to Home.\r\n','','','475306',1,'2014-09-14 23:36:28'),(172,44,'Day 1 : Bellary-Hospet-Kishkinda-Hospet','Day11410718073.jpeg','Arrival in Bellary. Meet and Greet  proceed to Hospet(60 Km/1-2 Hrs). Check in to Hotel Later Lunch Proceed to Visit to Kishkinda(20 Km/1/2 Hrs), The Famous Place of Ramayana Where the Lord Rama Approached to Sugreeva Along with His Brother Laxamna,  spend the evening enjoying the garden’s of the Tunga Bhadra Dam Area. Back to Hotel After Dinner Overnight at Hotel.\r\n','','','996153',1,'2014-09-14 23:37:53'),(173,44,'Day 2 : Hospet - Hampi (12 kms/1/2 Hours) –Depart to Hospet','Day21410718098.jpg','This Day After Breakfast Proceed for Sightseeing of Hampi Viist to Virupaksha Swamy Temple and Museum, Vijaya Vittala Temple, Mhanavami Dibba, Narasimha Swamy Temple,Hazara Rama Temple, Royal Palace,Raghunath Temple. In the Evening we will Depart to  Hospet Bus Station  for Back to Home.\r\n','','','280542',1,'2014-09-14 23:38:18'),(174,45,'Day 01	:	Calicut – Wayanad (65 kms/1-2 hrs)','Day11410718147.jpg','Transfer to Wayanad, home to exotic legends and ancient mysterious mountain caves, jungle trails and exotic wildlife. Being traditionally more or less isolated from rest of Kerala, the region has a distinctive character of its own.  Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','704257',1,'2014-09-14 23:39:07'),(175,45,'Day 02	:	Wayanad','Day21410718169.jpg','This morning you will proceed on a sightseeing tour of Wayanad visiting the Chain Tree, Neelimala View Point, Sultan Battery, Jain Temple and Edakkal Caves.  Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','938628',1,'2014-09-14 23:39:29'),(176,45,'Day 03	:	Wayanad – Calicut (65 kms/2 hrs)','day31410718191.jpg','Transfer to Calicut Back to Home journey\r\n','','','351525',1,'2014-09-14 23:39:51'),(177,107,'Day 01	:	 Jaipur','Day11410863143.JPG','Arrive Jaipur. Transfer to your hotel. This afternoon you will tour the city of Jaipur visit the City Palace, an overwhelming complex of exquisite palaces, gardens and courtyards. Visit the palace museum that houses collections of rare manuscripts, armory, costumes, carpets and miniature paintings. Walk to the adjacent Jantarmantar an astronomical observatory built in 17th century. Lastly you will drive past the Hawa Mahal, a Palace of winds. Overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','975600',1,'2014-09-16 15:55:43'),(178,107,'Day 02	:	 Jaipur','Day21410863191.jpg','This morning visit Amer fort an ancient capital of Jaipur, you will see magnificent palaces with walls covered with mirrored mosaics. Enjoy an elephant ride at the Amer fort. Rest of the day is at leisure for shopping and own activities, overnight  at the hotel\r\n','','','734956',1,'2014-09-16 15:56:31'),(179,107,'Day 03	:	 Jaipur –Ajmer-Pushker-Udaipur  (450  kms/6 – 7 hrs)','Day31410863229.jpg','Early this morning you will drive to Udaipur, en-route you will stop to visit the holy towns of Pushkar & Ajmer. Visit the Pushkar Lake & a Brahma temple in Pushkar, while in Ajmer visit the Dargah of Salim Chisti. Arrive Udaipur Check in to Hotel Overnight at Udaipur.  \r\n','','','958960',1,'2014-09-16 15:57:09'),(180,107,'Day 04	:	 Udaipur  (335 kms/7 – 8  hrs)','Day41410863275.jpg','This morning After Breakfast  proceed for a sightseeing tour of Udaipur visit to the City palace  and museum, proceed to Jagdish temple and lastly visit the Sahelion Ki Bari “Gardens of the Maidens”. In the evening you will be Free for leisure Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel.\r\n','','','469955',1,'2014-09-16 15:57:55'),(181,107,'Day 05	:	 Udaipur-Mount Abu(175 km/2-3 Hrs)','Day51410863322.jpg','This day After Breakfast we will transferred  by road to Mount Abu, the Only Hill Station in Rajasthan at an Altitude of 1,220mts. crowning the highest peak of the Aravali Hills .On arrive Mount abu check in to Hotel Later Afternoon you will  visit the magnificent Dilwara Jain Temples built in 11th century, sunset point, Nakki Lake. In the Evening  Free for Leisure Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel.\r\n','','','338627',1,'2014-09-16 15:58:42'),(182,107,'Day 06 	:	MountAbu- Jodhpur','Day61410863369.jpg','This day After Breakfast we will transferred by road to Jodhapur  en-route stopping at Ranakpur, a famous Jain pilgrimage destination known for its exquisitely carved Jain temples and most famous hall of 1444 pillars  on Arrive Jodhpur Check in to Hotel. Overnight  at Hotel.\r\n','','','159907',1,'2014-09-16 15:59:29'),(183,107,'Day 07	:	 Jodhpur','Day71410863413.jpg','This day After Breakfast  proceed for a sightseeing tour of Jodhpur, visit the Majestic Mehrangarh Fort, sprawled across a 125 meter high hill and is the most impressive and formidable fort in the fort-studded Rajasthan, continue to Jaswant Thada a cluster of Royal cenotaphs built in 1899, lastly visit the Umaid Bhavan Palace and museum. Rest of the day is at leisure for shopping and individual activities, Back to Hotel.  Overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','990773',1,'2014-09-16 16:00:13'),(184,107,'Day 08	:	Jodhpur – Jaisalmer (285 kms/5-6 hrs)','Day81410863450.jpg','Drive to Golden city of Jaisalmer. Arrive and proceed to your hotel. Rest of the day is at leisure to explore this golden city on your own\r\n','','','105104',1,'2014-09-16 16:00:50'),(185,107,'Day 09	:	 Jaisalmer','Day91410863497.jpg','Morning visit to the Jaisalmer fort, only fort in India which has a population of  thousand people living within its walls, later visit to the countless havelis spread across Jaisalmer which are reputed as the city’s real showpieces. Late evening you will visit the Sand Dunes to witness a spectacular sunset over the sand dunes, overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','640337',1,'2014-09-16 16:01:37'),(186,107,'Day 10	:	 Jaiselmer – Bikaner  (321 kms/4 – 5 hrs)','Day101410863541.jpg','Early this morning you will drive to the imposing walled city of Bikaner, Late afternoon you will visit the unusual Junagarh Fort; only fort in Rajasthan built on the desert plains itself , lastly visit the National Camel Breeding Farm and see the incredible sight of a herd of camels returning back after grazing, with the spectacular desert sunset in the background. Overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','802418',1,'2014-09-16 16:02:21'),(187,107,'Day 11	: Depart to Bikaner/Jaipur','Day111410863590.jpg','This day After Breakfast we will Depart to Bikaner/Jaipur Rly stn /Airport\r\n','','','571505',1,'2014-09-16 16:03:10'),(188,46,'Day 1 : Srinagar','Day11410933033.jpg','On arrive at Srinagar  a Lake city of Kashmir, located in the heart of the Kashmir valley at an altitude of 1,730 m above sea level, famous for its lakes dotted with Shikaras,  and the Mughal Gardens. Meet and Greet  Transfer to hotel. This afternoon visit the world famous Mughal gardens built by Emperor Jehangir. Enjoy a ‘Shikara ride’ on the picturesque Dal lake. Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel.\r\n','','','988805',1,'2014-09-17 11:20:33'),(189,46,'Day 2	:     Srinagar - Gulmarg - Srinagar (55 kms/1-2 hrs one way)','Day21410933093.jpg','This morning proceed for a full day excursion to Gulmarg, a Meadow of Flowers situated at an altitude of 2730 meters, and a famous ski resort duringthe winters. Enjoy leisurely walks \r\non the lush green meadows of flowers with a backdrop of the snow capped mountains OR enjoy an optional Gondola ride (Cable Car), Khilanmarg . Back to Hotel Over night at Hotel.','','','383198',1,'2014-09-17 11:21:33'),(190,46,'Day 3   :           Srinagar - Pahalgam - SriNagar (95 kms/3 -4  hrs)','Day31410933149.jpg','Today you will be transferred 