ill visit the famous ghat of Hari ki Paudi to witness an evening Ganga Aarti ceremony, overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','642025',1,'2014-09-17 12:25:14'),(251,56,'Day 5	:	Haridwar - Mussorie (80 kms/2- 2.5 hrs)','Day5_at_kemptyfalls-mussoorie1410936984.jpg','Early this morning you may visit to Ganga ghats for a holy dip in the Ganges River. Later this morning you will be transferred by road to Mussorie, Located in the foothills of the Himalayas, Mussoorie gets its name from the Mansur shrub that is commonly seen in the hill resort and often referred to as the \"Queen of the Hills\".Arrive and proceed to your hotel, rest of the day is at leisure to explore this hill town on your own, overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','383617',1,'2014-09-17 12:26:24'),(252,56,'Day 6	:	Mussorie','Day6_at_Garhwal1410937014.jpg','This day is at leisure to explore this charming hill station of Garhwal on your own or simply take a stroll on the Mall road, the most happening place in Mussorie, overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','750461',1,'2014-09-17 12:26:54'),(253,56,'Day 7	:	Mussorie - Delhi (280 kms/ 7 - 8 hrs)','Day7_at_delhi1410937067.jpg','Today you will be transferred to New Delhi,  arrive and proceed to airport/railway station for Back to Home.\r\n','','','957952',1,'2014-09-17 12:27:47'),(254,57,'Day 1 : Delhi - Mussorie (280 kms / 7-8 hrs)','Day1_at_doon valley1410937303.jpg','Arrive Delhi and you will be transferred by road to Mussorie, situated at an altitude of 2000 meters. and offers some breathtaking views of snow clad Himalayan peaks of the western Garhwal as well as the Doon valley. Proceed to your hotel and rest of the day at leisure, overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','394978',1,'2014-09-17 12:31:43'),(255,57,'Day 2 : Mussorie','Day2_at_kempty-falls1410937345.jpg','This you will proceed on a local sightseeing tour of Mussorie, visit Kempty Falla, Tibetan Monastery, lastly visit the Gun Hill situated on the Mall road offering breathtaking views  of the Himalayas, enjoy an