tel. Rest of the day is at leisure for individual activities, overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','140457',1,'2014-09-17 12:39:11'),(266,58,'Day 6 : Rudraprayag','Day6_at_Dhanaulti1410938041.jpg','This day is at leisure to visit the temples in and around Rudraprayag  later you will be transferred to Mussorie, the Queen of hill Station. Enroute you will drive via Dhanaulti & the Kempty waterfalls. Arrive and proceed to your hotel, rest of the evening is at leisure, overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','933276',1,'2014-09-17 12:39:38'),(267,58,'Day 7 : Mussorie','Day7_at_Mussoorie-mall-road-in-evening1410938612.jpg','This day is at leisure to explore this charming hill station of Garhwal on your own or simply take a stroll on the Mall road, the most happening place in Mussorie, overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','483826',1,'2014-09-17 12:53:32'),(268,58,'Day 8 : Mussorie - Delhi (280 kms/ 7 - 8 hrs)','Day8_at_Delhi1410938674.jpg','Today you will be transferred to New Delhi,  arrive and proceed to airport/railway station\r\n','','','902642',1,'2014-09-17 12:54:34'),(269,59,'Day 01 : Delhi - Haridwar (228 kms/5-6 hrs)','Day1_at_Hari ki Paudi1410938744.jpg','This morning you will be transferred to Haridwar, on the right bank of River Ganga at the feet of Shivalik ranges, an ancient pilgrim city is one of the holiest places for Hindus. Arrive and proceed to your hotel. Later this evening you will visit the famous ghat of Hari ki Paudi to witness an evening Ganga Aarti ceremony, overnight at the hotel.\r\n','','','317199',1,'2014-09-17 12:55:44'),(270,59,'Day 02 : Haridwar - Mussorie (80 kms/2- 2.5 hrs)','Day2_at_mussoorie1410938835.jpg','Early this morning you may visit to Ganga ghats for a holy dip in the Ganges River. Later this morning you will be transferred by road to Mussorie, Located in the foothills of the Himalayas, Mussoorie gets its name from the Mansur shrub that is commonly seen in the hill resort and often referred to as the \"Queen of the Hills\".Arrive and proceed to your hotel, rest of the day is at leisure to explore this hill town on your own, overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','738612',1,'2014-09-17 12:57:15'),(271,59,'Day 03 : Mussorie','Day3_at_Mussoorie-mall-road-in-evening1410938863.jpg','This day is at leisure to explore this charming hill station of Garhwal on your own or simply take a stroll on the Mall road, the most happening place in Mussorie, overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','369877',1,'2014-09-17 12:57:43'),(272,59,'Day 04 : Mussorie - Delhi (280 kms/ 7 - 8 hrs)','Day4_at_delhi1410938893.jpg','Today you will be transferred to New Delhi,  arrive and proceed to airport/railway station for Back to Home.\r\n','','','122723',1,'2014-09-17 12:58:13'),(273,60,'Day 1 : Arrive Delhi','Day1_at_qutub-minar-delhi1410938951.jpg','Arrive Delhi transfer to your hotel. This afternoon you will proceed for a sightseeing tour of Old & New Delhi, visit the  visit the Qutub Minar, tallest stone tower in India. Drive past the imposing India Gate and the Rastrapathi Bhawan, Red fort & Jama Masjid. Evening is at leisure, optionally you may visit the Red fort for sound and light show. Overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','424626',1,'2014-09-17 12:59:11'),(274,60,'Day 2 : Delhi - Agra  (206 kms/3-4 hrs)','Day2_at_agra1410938981.jpg','Today you will drive to Mughal city Agra. Arrive and check into your hotel. This afternoon visit the Agra fort, Built by the great Emperor Akbar, proceed to the Taj Mahal, built by Emperor Shah Jahan in memory of his wife Mumtaz Mahal. This evening is at leisure for shopping and individual activities.  Overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','181792',1,'2014-09-17 12:59:41'),(275,60,'Day 3 : Agra - Jaipur (236 kms/5 - 6  hrs)','Day3_Fatehpur_Sikri_Panch_Mahal1410939015.jpg','This morning you will drive to the pink city of Jaipur, enroute you will stop to visit  Fatehpur Sikri, the deserted red sandstone city built by the  Mughal Emperor Akbar. Proceed to your hotel rest of the day is at leisure. This evening you may optionally visit to Chokhi Dhani, an ethnic Rajaasthani village located on the outskirts of Jaipur, overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','663002',1,'2014-09-17 13:00:15'),(276,60,'Day 4 : Jaipur','Day4_Sunrise light over Amber Fort in Jaipur1410939049.jpg','This morning visit the Amber fort, built in 16th century, enjoy an elephant ride at Amber. Drive past the Hawa Mahal, a Palace of winds. In the afternoon you will visit the city palace and museum, walk to adjacent Jantar Mantar an astronomical observatory.  Rest of the evening is at leisure, overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','786970',1,'2014-09-17 13:00:49'),(277,60,'Day 5 : Depart Jaipur (258 kms / 5 - 6 hrs)','Day5_at_Jaipur-City-from-Nahargarh-Fort11410939086.jpg','Transfer to airport/railway stations OR transfer by road  to Delhi.\r\n','','','146314',1,'2014-09-17 13:01:26'),(278,61,'Day 1 : Delhi - Chandigarh(250 kms / 5-6 hrs)','Day1_at_Boating at Sukuna Lake1410939142.jpg','On arrive at Delhi Airport Meet and Greet Transferred to  Chandigarh The Joint Capital of Punjab and Haryana Arrive  Chandigarh Check in to Hotel  Later Afternoon visit to Rock Garden and Rose Garden in the Evening Boating at Sukuna Lake Optional you may shopping at Sector 17 Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel.\r\n','','','187861',1,'2014-09-17 13:02:22'),(279,61,'Day 2 : Chandigarh - Manali (280 kms / 7- 8 hrs)','Day2_Arrive Manali1410939177.jpg','Today you will proceed by road to Manali a picture-perfect hill resort at an altitude of 1,929 metres. Set amidst pine-clad mountains, which gradually close in on both sides of the Beas and nestling in their shade, as though carved out of primeval forest, is a scattered hamlet, which comprises this picturesque summer resort. Proceed to your hotel. Rest of the evening is at leisure, overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','410297',1,'2014-09-17 13:02:57'),(280,61,'Day 3 : Manali','Day3_bottom_Solang Valley1410939214.jpg','This morning you will visit the Solang Valley, which offers fine views of glaciers and snow, capped peaks. A place not to be missed is Rohtang Pass, 51 km from Manali at an altitude of 3978 meters (subject to weather conditions). In the Evening proceed for a walking tour of Manali, visit the 450 years old temple dedicated to Hadimba Devi, which has some excellent woodcarving. Visit the Tibetan Monastery and a handicraft center. Rest of the day at leisure OR optionally you may walk to nearby picturesque village of Vashisht known for hot sulphur springs. Overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','813421',1,'2014-09-17 13:03:34'),(281,61,'Day 4 : Manali -  Dharamshala ( 200 km/6-7hrs)','Day4_at the Baijnath temple1410939249.jpg','This morning  After breakfast you will transferred to you Dharamshala , En-route visit the Baijnath temple, one of the 12 Jyotirlingas. Arrive Dharamshala Rest of the evening over night at hotel.\r\n','','','532971',1,'2014-09-17 13:04:09'),(282,61,'Day 5 : Dharamshala','Day5_Maclodgunj Markets1410939281.JPG','This morning you will proceed for half day excursion to Later this afternoon you will visit the Tibetan monastery in Maclodganj (upper Dharamshala) a seat of Tibetan spiritual leader Dalai Lama. Rest of the day is at leisure explore local Tibetan markets at the Maclodgunj, overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','266169',1,'2014-09-17 13:04:41'),(283,61,'Day 6 : Dharamshala - Amritsar (195 kms/4-5 hrs)','Day6_at_golden-temple1410939310.jpg','This Day After Breakfast you will proceed to  Amritsar Golden city of Punjab Arrive Check in Hotel Rest of the Evening visit to Waghborder Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel.\r\n','','','262820',1,'2014-09-17 13:05:10'),(284,61,'Day 7 : Depart to Amritsar ','Day7_at_Jalianwalabag1410939335.jpg','This day After Breakfast visit to Golden Temple and Jalianwalabagh later after noon we will Depart to Amritsar/Delhi Airport for Back to Home.\r\n','','','939745',1,'2014-09-17 13:05:35'),(285,70,'Day 01 : Arrive Cochin-Munnar','Day1_at_munnar1410942571.jpg','On arrive at Trichur Rly stn Meet and\r\nGreet Proceed to Munnar, a picture book towns and winding lanes, Munnar\r\nis one of the most exotic of hill stations of Kerala. Rest of the day is at leisure.\r\nOvernight at hotel.\r\n','','','125780',1,'2014-09-17 13:59:31'),(286,70,'Day 02 : Munnar','DAy2_at_Muttupetty dam1410942608.jpg','This morning you will proceed on a sightseeing tour of the picturesque Munnar, visit Raja Malai, a top peak of Munnar where you can see Neel Thar (mountain goats), Muttupetty dam. Continue your tour to Echo Point. Rest of the day is at leisure, overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','835311',1,'2014-09-17 14:00:08'),(287,70,'Day 03 : Munnar - Thekady (120 kms/ 3-4 hrs)','Day3+at_ Thekkady1410942641.jpg','Transfer to Thekady. Situated at an altitude of 900-1800 mtrs. The very sound of the word Thekkady conjures up images of elephants, unending chains of hills and spice scented plantations. This evening enjoy a boat safari on Periyar Lake to view the varied wild life of this region. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','281372',1,'2014-09-17 14:00:41'),(288,70,'Day 04 : Thekkady - Allepphy - Kettuvalam(House Boat)(130kms/3-4hrs)','Day4_at_Kettuvalam1410942672.gif','Today you will board a Kettuvalam the famous Houseboats of Kerala. Cruise through the unique web of lakes, lagoons, canals, rivers and India’s most enchanting areas - a rural, riverine expanse of verdant coconut groves and rice paddies. Overnight onboard Houseboat.\r\n','','','730736',1,'2014-09-17 14:01:12'),(289,70,'Day 05 : Kettuvalam - Alleppey - Kanyakumari (193 kms/ 5-6  hrs)','Day5_at_kannyakumari_beach1410942705.jpg','This morning you will disembark at the Alleppey boat jetty and will be transferred by road to Kanyakumari, the land&#39;s end of India or the point where the three seas meet, is the enchanting Kanyakumari. Witness a spectacular sunset over the Arabian Sea. Overnight at hotel\r\n','','','210029',1,'2014-09-17 14:01:45'),(290,70,'Day 06 : Kanyakumari - Kovalam (53 kms / 2 hrs)','Day6_at_Kanyakumari1410942735.JPG','Early this morning you will experience the  magnificent sunrise over Bay of Bengal. Proceed by road to Kovalam, so perfect a beach, it’s almost a picture postcard cliche: age old black rocks, towering palms, sands and gentle surf. Rest of the day at leisure, Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','887340',1,'2014-09-17 14:02:15'),(291,70,'Day 07 : Kovalam - Trivandrum (13 Kms / 30 minutes)','Day7_at_Kovalam Beach11410942771.jpg','This day we will Depart to Trivandrum Intl Airport For Back to Home                                                                ','','','222449',1,'2014-09-17 14:02:51'),(292,71,'Day 01	:	  Kochi - Munnar (130 kms / 4 - 5 hrs)','Day1_at_munnar tea garden1410942862.jpg','Upon arrival at Kochi transfer to Munnar one of the most popular hill stations in southern India known for its sprawling tea gardens. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','430857',1,'2014-09-17 14:04:22'),(293,71,'Day 02 : Munnar','Day2_at_mattupetty-dam1410942885.jpg','This morning you will proceed on a sightseeing tour of the picturesque Mattupetty Dam, where you have an opportunity to go boating. Continue your tour to Echo Point. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','141219',1,'2014-09-17 14:04:45'),(294,71,'Day 03 : Munnar - Thekkady (120 kms / 3 - 4 hrs)','Day3_periyar-wildlife-sanctuary1410942924.jpg','Transfer to Thekkady, Set in the heart of the Cardamom Hills of Kerala, is the Periyar National Park and Tiger Reserve, offering a rare opportunity to enjoy South India’s wild life. Enjoy a boat safari on Periyar lake to view the varied wild life of this region. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','473758',1,'2014-09-17 14:05:24'),(295,71,'Day 04 : Thekkady - Kumarakom (130 kms/3-4 hrs)','Day4_vembanad-lake1410942977.jpg','Today you will be transferred by road to Kumarakom, a charming village on the Vembanad Lake, enroute you will stop to see the spice plantations. Proceed to your island home in-time to view the spectacular sunset. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','818894',1,'2014-09-17 14:06:17'),(296,71,'Day 05 : Kumarakom','Day5_at_kumarakom-backwaters1410943015.jpg','The day is at leisure to explore the backwaters, known for its small water canals surrounded by lush green paddy fields and swaying palms OR pamper yourself with some Ayurvedic beauty treatments. Overnight at  hotel.\r\n','','','907261',1,'2014-09-17 14:06:55'),(297,71,'Day 6 : Kumarakom - Kochi (90 kms/2 hrs)','Day6_at_Chinese fishing nets1410943202.jpg','Transfer by road to Kochi, the  gateway to <b>Gods Own Country</b>. This afternoon you visit the Jewish Synagogue, Dutch Palace and end your tour with a visit to the Chinese fishing nets. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','205267',1,'2014-09-17 14:10:02'),(298,71,'Day 7 : Depart Kochi','Day7_Kochi_Bypass_Vytila1410943245.jpg','Transfer from your hotel to airport / railway station.\r\n','','','861864',1,'2014-09-17 14:10:45'),(299,72,'Day 01 : Arrive Cochin','DAy1_at_0jewish-Synagogue1410943309.jpg','Arrive Kochi, The commercial capital and the most cosmopolitan city of Kerala, Kochi along with its mainland part, Ernakulam, is also known as the Queen of the Arabian Sea. This afternoon you will visit the Jewish Synagogue, the Dutch Palace, the Chinese fishing nets. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','519943',1,'2014-09-17 14:11:49'),(300,72,'Day 02 : Cochin-Allepphy - Kettuvalam(House Boat)(40kms/1-2hrs)','Day2_at_Kettuvalam_kerala1410943341.jpg','Today you will board a Kettuvalam the famous Houseboats of Kerala. Cruise through the unique web of lakes, lagoons, canals, rivers and India’s most enchanting areas - a rural, riverine expanse of verdant coconut groves and rice paddies. Overnight onboard Houseboat\r\n','','','116541',1,'2014-09-17 14:12:21'),(301,72,'Day 03 : Allepphy - Munnar (130 kms / 4-5 hrs)','Day3_at_munnar1410943371.jpg','This Day 09:00 Am Disembark  Allepphy House boat to be transferred by road to Munnar, a picture-book towns and winding lanes, Munnar is one of the most exotic of hill stations of Kerala. Rest of the day is at