g','After breakfast drive to Bhuj, Upon arrival proceed to DSP/Collector office to obtain the permit ( Please all foreign clients need to obtain the permit for Banny village visit) ** Note : 2nd & 4th Saturday & Public holidays are closed at DSP/COLLECTOR office hence set the dates accordingly.\r\nEvening visit to the Bhuj city and market Overnight at Hotel. \r\n','','','612823',1,'2014-09-17 17:22:20'),(404,100,'Day 03 : Bhuj - Fullday visit to the Banny ','Day31410954774.jpg','villages (150 Kms / 4 Hours onway)\r\nFull day excursion to the White Rann Of Kutch. In the Evening return to Bhuj hotel for overnight at Hotel.\r\n','','','710050',1,'2014-09-17 17:22:54'),(405,100,'Day 04 : Bhuj - Rajkot (260 Kms)','Day41410954806.jpg','After breakfast drive to Rajkot,Visit to Mahatma Gandhi House and Watson Museum Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel.\r\n','','','819317',1,'2014-09-17 17:23:26'),(406,100,'Day 05 : Rajkot-Ahmedabad(250 Km/3-4 Hrs) ','Day51410954862.jpg','This Day After Breakfast  Proceed for Ahmedabad Check in to Hotel Later LunchProceed for Sightseeing of Ahmadabad Visit to  visiting Dakorji Temple (Temple of Lord Krishna) later Afternoon Visit to Akshardham Temple at Gandhinagar in the Evening Free for Leisure Optional you may visit to CG Road and Law Garden Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel.\r\n','','','405267',1,'2014-09-17 17:24:22'),(407,0,'','','','','','',1,'2014-09-17 17:25:51'),(408,100,'Day 06: Depart to Ahmadabad','Day61410955096.jpg','This Day After Breakfast we will Depart to Ahmedabad Airport/Rly stn for Back to Home.\r\n','','','697077',1,'2014-09-17 17:28:16'),(409,96,'Day 01 :Shiridi','Day11410955206.jpg','Arrive Shiridi the Holy pilgrimage of Holy Sai Baba Temple Arrive Check in to Hotel After Fresh up Proceed for Pooja and Dharshan of Lord Sai Baba Temple Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel.\r\n','','','627351',1,'2014-09-17 17:30:06'),(410,96,'Day 02 : Shiridi-Shanisighanipur-Nasik-Trimbakeshwar-Shiridi','Day21410955243.jpg','This day After Breakfast  you will proceed for Pooja and Dhrshan of Shanisinghani pur of  Lord Shani and Nasik panchwati temple , Trimbakeshwar( one of the 12 jyothirlingas) Back to Shiridi Overnight at Shiridi.\r\n','','','185008',1,'2014-09-17 17:30:43'),(411,96,'Day 03 : Shirdi - Aurangabad - Ajanta ','Day31410955275.jpg','In the morning, after breakfast you will be driven to Aurangabad (130 kms- 3 hrs). On arrival check in into hotel. Afternoon we proceed for excursion of 105 kms – 2hrs to witness famous Ajanta caves. Ajanta is one of the few historical and architectural marvels of India. Recognized as the World Heritage site today, it was discovered during the 19th century by a group of British officers who were on a tiger hunt. The Ajanta group of caves, located deep within the Sahyadri hills above the Waghora, depicts the story of Buddhism that prevailed here during 200 BC to 650 AD. After visiting Ajanta Caves drive back to Aurangabad. Return to Aurangabad for overnight\r\n','','','998543',1,'2014-09-17 17:31:15'),(412,96,'Day 04 : Aurangabad - Ellora','Day41410955305.jpg','After breakfast take a sight seeing tour of Ellora – 30 kms, ½ hours, one of the highly visited World heritage sites of India. It houses 34 monasteries and temples with some exclusive uninterrupted sequence of monuments that date back from 600 to 1000 AD. The temples of Ellora is dedicated to Brahmanism, Jainism, and Buddhism. It also has some of the excellent stonework depicting the legends related to Lord Shiva. Also visit to Grishneshwar Temple(one of the 12 Jyothirlingas).Back to Hotel Overnight at Hotel..\r\n','','','830981',1,'2014-09-17 17:31:45'),(413,96,'Day 05 : Aurangabad ','Day51410955327.jpg','This day After Breakfast we will Depart to Aurangabad rlystn/Airport for  Back to  Home.\r\n','','','509497',1,'2014-09-17 17:32:07'),(414,94,'Day 01	: 	Arrive Bhubaneswar','Day1_Lingaraj_temple_Bhubaneswar1411973022.jpg','Arrive Bhubaneswar. You will be met upon arrival & transferred to your hotel. Rest of the day is at leisure to explore this ancient city of Kalinga on your own, overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','596671',1,'2014-09-29 12:13:42'),(415,94,'Day 02	:	Bhubaneswar','Day2_at_Mukteswara temple1411973057.jpg','This morning proceed for a sightseeing tour of Bhubaneshwar, you will visit  Lingaraj Temple dedicated to Lord Shiva built in the 11th century, proceed to Mukteswara temple built in the 10th century known for its sculpted tales from the Panchatantra carved on it, the temple is a magnificent example of Orissan architecture continue to The Rajarani temple set in picturesque surrounding is noted for its intricate carvings of floral, animal and human figures built in the 11th century.\r\n<br>\r\nAfternoon visit Caves- Khandagiri and Udaygiri hills were carved and tunneled, to create this multi-storied ancient apartment residence for Jain monks. They were the work of the first known Orissan ruler, King Kharavela, and probably begun in the first century BC. Overnight at the hotel. ','','','576974',1,'2014-09-29 12:14:17'),(416,94,'Day 03	:	Bhuvaneshwar - Dhauli - Pipli - Konark - Puri  (70 kms/3-4 hrs)','Day3_Dhauli1411973195.jpg','Today you will proceed to Puri, enroute you will visit, Dhauli-The battleground of Kalinga war during 3rd century BC, which transformed Emperor Ashoka into Dharmashoka, visit .Buddhist Peace Pagoda, built in 1970s.Famous for Ashokan Rock Edict and the Dhabaleswar Temple. Later visit Pipli village, famous for brilliant applique work known for its folk character and vitality. \r\nLater you will visit Konarak- world heriage site -The temple chariot of the Sun God on the sands of Bay of Bengal is a 13th century architectural marvel. It is designed as a celestial chariot of Sun God, complete with twelve pairs of wheel and seven horses. This legendary temple has sculptures of great beauty covering all aspects of life. It is most famous for its erotic art. Later drive to Puri and proceed to your hotel. Overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','267965',1,'2014-09-29 12:16:35'),(417,94,'Day 04	:	Puri ','Day4_Golden_beach_puri1411973228.jpg','This morning you will visit Puri-the city by the sea- is a major pilgrim center in India, founded by .Adi Shankara and is one of the peethas here. Puri is also famous for its Golden beach ideal for swimming and surfing. But the fame of Puri emanates most from the Jagannath Temple, which contributed the word Jurrernaut to the English language. Rest of the day is at leisure on the beach, overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','316209',1,'2014-09-29 12:17:08'),(418,94,'Day 05	:	Puri - Saora - Rayagada','Day5_Saora_Rayagada1411974530.jpg','Today you will begin with your Tribal tour with a visit to Rayagada, enroute you will be visiting Saora Tribe and villages, The whole area is an intricate labyrinth of precipitous hills and valleys, which are part of the Eastern Ghat-the height of the hills varying from 2000 to 4000 sqft above sea level. They trace their origin to the Ramayana there is a reference of Savari, a Saora women whom Ram and Laxman met while moving about in the Dandaka forests in search of Sita. Visit also the local tribal market. Proceed to your hotel and rest of the day is at leisure, overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','451942',1,'2014-09-29 12:17:49'),(419,94,'Day 06	:	Rayagada','Day6_Dukum village1411973300.jpg','Today you will proceed for a full day excursion to Bissam Cuttack to visit the Kutia Kondh and their weekly tribal market at Dukum village. The most important aspect of Kondh tribal tribal culture is the music and dance. Among certain tribes young men cannot find brides unless they acquire special skill in dance and music. Dance and music are primarily meant to propitiate Gods and Goddesses. In social functions like marriage and feasting dance is their usual hobby. The dance is performed in a central place of the village or in the communal house and attended by almost all the tribesmen. Each tribe has it own pattern of dance and music. Overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','907244',1,'2014-09-29 12:18:20'),(420,94,'Day 07	: 	Rayagada - Jeypore','Day7_Chatikona Market1411973332.jpg','Today  you will visit to the tribal market of Dhongira kondh, you will leave for Chatikona to visit the weekly tribal maket of Dongria kondh tribe (Weekly market is held every Wednesday). After visit leave for Jeypore en route visiting desai kondh tribe, village and their weekly tribal market. The Kondhs are known in the history for their Meriah Sacrifice-Human Sacrifice. The Kondhs are of a Dravidian origin and speak Kuvi language. They practice elaborate birth, marriage and death rituals.Arrive and proceed to your hotel, rest of the evening is at leisure, overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','433867',1,'2014-09-29 12:18:52'),(421,94,'Day 08	:	Jeypore','Day8_at_Bondo1411973359.jpg','Full day visit of famed Bonda tribe and their weekly market (This is held at Onukudelli.This is an intense market situated on the hilly main street of this tiny town. The Bonda has been described as the wildest, rudest and possibly the most interesting tribe. Known as the naked people, the Bonda are a fascinating group. They are named after the Bonda hills of Orissa’s interior and are known for their stubborn, independent and often ferocious spirit. Overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','139503',1,'2014-09-29 12:19:19'),(422,94,'Day 09	:	Jeypore - Gupteswar - Vishakapatnam ','Day9_at_Gupteswar Cave1411973398.JPG','Today you will proceed to Vishakapatnam enroute you will visit Gupteswar Cave and  Dhurva Tribe Gupteswar is a famous cave shrine dedicated to Lord Shiva and located at the top of a limestone hill which is about 500 mts above sea level.Surrounded by a dense forest of sal trees and flanked by Kolab river. Arrive and proceed to your hotel, rest of the day is at leisure, overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','597660',1,'2014-09-29 12:19:58'),(423,94,'Day 10	:	Depart Vishakhapatnam ','Day10_Simachalam Temple1411973421.jpg','Today you will visit the famous Simachalam Temple Simachalam is a temple of the &#39;Narashima Avatar&#39;,it is situated on the small hill Simachala on the outskirts of Vishak. Later you will proceed to airport/railway station for your onward journey. \r\n','','','190953',1,'2014-09-29 12:20:21'),(424,92,'Day 01: Arrive Bhubaneswar','Day1_at_Lingaraj Temple1411973617.jpg','Arrive Bhubaneswar, the Capital city of the modern State and the ancient kingdom of Kalinga. You will be met upon arrival & transferred to your hotel. This afternoon you will proceed for the city sightseeing tour of Bhubaneswar, visit  Lingaraj Temple dedicated to Lord Shiva built in the 11th century, proceed to Mukteswara temple built in the 10th century known for its sculpted tales from the Panchatantra carved on it, the temple is a magnificent example of Orissan architecture continue to The Rajarani temple set in picturesque surrounding is noted for its intricate carvings of floral, animal and human figures built in the 11th century. Rest of the evening is at leisure for individual activities, Also  visit Nandankanan Bilogical Park, The picturesque Nandankanan, or the Garden of the Gods, is a beautiful biological park, 20 kms from Bhubaneshwar, established in 1960. The park houses the very first captive gharial breeding centre of the country. The zoo at Nandakanan is world-renowned for its white tigers, enjoy an optional  aerial ropeway and cable car, visit Caves- Khandagiri and Udaygiri hills were carved and tunneled, to create this multi-storied ancient apartment residence for Jain monks. They were the work of the first known Orissan ruler, King Kharavela, and probably begun in the first century BC Overnight at the hotel.\r\n','','','215570',1,'2014-09-29 12:23:37'),(425,92,'Day 02	:	Bhuvaneshwar - Dhauli - Pipli - Konark - Puri  (70 kms/3-4 hrs)','Day2_Konark_sun_temple1411973689.jpg','Today you will proceed to Puri, enroute you will visit, Dhauli-The battleground of Kalinga war during 3rd century BC, which transformed Emperor Ashoka into Dharmashoka, visit .Buddhist Peace Pagoda, built in 1970s.Famous for Ashokan Rock Edict and the Dhabaleswar Temple. Later visit Pipli village, famous for brilliant applique work known for its folk character and vitality. \r\nLater you will visit Konarak- world heriage site -The temple chariot of the Sun God on the sands of Bay of Bengal is a 13th century architectural marvel. It is designed as a celestial chariot of Sun God, complete with twelve pairs of wheel and seven horses. This legendary temple has sculptures of great beauty covering all aspects of life. It is most famous for its erotic art. Later drive to Puri and proceed to your hotel. Overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','806565',1,'2014-09-29 12:24:49'),(426,92,'Day 03	:	Puri ','Day3_Shri_Jagannath_Temple_Puri1411974021.jpg','This morning you will visit Puri-the city by the sea- is a major pilgrim center in India, founded by .Adi Shankara and is one of the peethas here. Puri is also famous for its Golden beach ideal for swimming and surfing. But the fame of Puri emanates most from the Jagannath Temple, which contributed the word Jurrernaut to the English language. Rest of the day is at leisure on the beach, overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','407190',1,'2014-09-29 12:30:21'),(427,92,'Day 04 :	Puri  - Chilka Lake - Puri ','Day4_at_Chilka Lake1411974213.jpg','This morning you will proceed on a full day excursion to visit the famous chilka lake- the largest brackish water lake in the country spreading over 1200 sqkms and famous for its migratory birds and irawadi dolphins. . It attracts a large number of migratory birds, like the flamingo, teal, bar headed goose, shoveller and white - bellied sea eagle. For bird-lovers, Chilika is best visited in winter when the migratory populations wing in from places as far as Siberia. Evening is at leisure for shopping and individual activities, Back to Puri overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','660116',1,'2014-09-29 12:33:33'),(428,92,'Day 05: Depart to Bhubaneshwar','Day5_Bhubaneshwar1411974245.jpg','This Day After Breakfast we will Depart to Bhubaneshar Rly Stn/Airport For Back to Home.\r\n','','','706689',1,'2014-09-29 12:34:05'),(429,93,'Day 01	 :	Arrive Bhopal  ','Day1_Taj-ul-Masajidbhopal1411974626.jpg','Arrive Bhopal, The picturesque city of Bhopal, set around a lake and is famous for its archaeological wealth. You will be met upon arrival and transferred to your hotel. Afternoon visit Shamla and Idgah Hills which offers some of the best views of Bhopal,  later visit Shaukat Mahal designed by a French Architect lastly visit elegant Sadar Manzil, Hall of Public Audience of the former rulers of Bhopal. Rest of the evening is at leisure for individual activities, overnight at the hotel. \r\n','','','759465',1,'2014-09-29 12:40:26'),(430,93,'Day 02	:	Bhopal - Sanchi - Vidisha - Bhopal (70 kms/2 hrs)','Day2_at_Ashoka Pillar1411974687.jpg','This morning visit Sanchi, only place to have distinction of having specimens of almost all kinds of Buddhist architectural forms, Stupas, Chaityas, Temples and Monastries and the finest examples of Buddhist creative art and sculpture in the country most popular being the Ashoka Pillar. Later proceed to Vidisha, once bustling city and important trade center in ancient times, Situated in the fork of the Betwa and Beas rivers, Vidisha include the ruins of a Brahmanical shrine - dedicated to Lord Vishnu, the first known example of the use of cement in India. Overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','453959',1,'2014-09-29 12:41:27'),(431,93,'Day 03	:	Bhopal - Bhimbetka - Bhopal','Day3_Bhimbetka Caves1411974729.jpg','Today visit to Bhimbetka Caves, which is an UNESCO declared World Heritage Site, there are over 700 rock shelters belonging to the Neolithic age. Paintings in over 500 caves depict the life of prehistoric cave dwellers. Rest of the day is at leisure for shopping and individual activities, overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','969712',1,'2014-09-29 12:42:09'),(432,93,'Day 04	:	Bhopal - Indore (190 kms/3-4 hs)','Day4_Indreshwar Temple1411974773.jpg','Today you will drive to Indore, Situated on the banks of the Rivers Saraswati and Khan, Indore was planned and founded by Rani Ahilyabai Holkar and derives its name from the 18th C. Indreshwar Temple. Proceed to your hotel. Afternoon visit, famous temple of Bada Ganapati and Kanch Mandir a Jain temple is an architectural marvel in glass. Overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','960161',1,'2014-09-29 12:42:53'),(433,93,'Day 05	:	Indore - Ujjain - Indore (55 kms/1-2 hrs One Way)','Day5_river Shipra1411974811.jpg','This morning you will proceed for a full day excursion to Ujjain, one of the greatest cities of ancient India, Situated on the banks of the river Shipra, Ujjain is one of the venues of the Kumbh Mela held every 12 years. Evening return to Indore. Overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','503140',1,'2014-09-29 12:43:31'),(434,93,'Day 06	:	Indore -  Mandu (100 kms/2-3 hrs)','Day6_Hindola Mahal1411974845.jpg','Proceed by road to Mandu, Perched along the Vindhya ranges at an altitude of 2,000 feet, with its natural defenses, was originally the fort capital of the Parmar rulers of Malwa. Afternoon visit Jahaz Mahal, a 120 mt long \"ship palace\" built between the two artificial lakes, Hindola Mahal, it derives its name of \"swinging palace\". Overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','860888',1,'2014-09-29 12:44:05'),(435,93,'Day 07	:	Mandu - Maheshwar - Omkareshwar - Indore (235 kms/7-8 hs)','DAy7_Maheshwar_MP1411974892.jpg','In the  morning proceed to Maheshwar (80 kms), glorious city at the dawn of Indian civilization, Today, Maheshwar is also known for its distinctive handwoven sarees called Maheshwari. Proceed to Omkareshwar (55 kms), the sacred island, shaped like the holiest of all Hindu symbols, &#39;Om&#39;, has drawn to it hundreds of generations of pilgrims. Following temple visit drive to Indore (100 kms). Overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','726052',1,'2014-09-29 12:44:52'),(436,93,'Day 08	:	Depart Indoare','Day8_at_Indore1411974919.jpeg','Transfer to airport/railway station for your onward journey\r\n','','','126536',1,'2014-09-29 12:45:19'),(437,91,'Day 01	:	Bhopal - Indore (190 kms/3-4 hs)','Day1_at_Kanch Mandir1411975044.jpg','On Arrive at Bhopal by AP Samapark Kranthi Exp on 08:00 AM Meet and Greet  drive to Indore, Situated on the banks of the Rivers Saraswati and Khan, Indore was planned and founded by Rani Ahilyabai Holkar and derives its name from the 18th C. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIndreshwar Temple. Proceed to your hotel. Afternoon visit, famous temple of Bada Ganapati and Kanch Mandir a Jain temple is an architectural marvel in glass. Overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','699062',1,'2014-09-29 12:47:24'),(438,91,'Day 02	:	Indore - Ujjain - Indore (55 kms/1-2 hrs One Way)','Day2_to Ujjain1411975090.jpg','This morning you will proceed for a full day excursion to Ujjain, one of the greatest cities of ancient India, Situated on the banks of the river Shipra, Ujjain is one of the venues of the Kumbh Mela held every 12 years. Evening return to Indore. Overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','382227',1,'2014-09-29 12:48:10'),(439,91,'Day 03	:	Indore - Maheshwar - Omkareshwar-Indore  (235 kms/7-8 hs)','Day3_omkareshwar1411975131.jpg','In the  morning proceed to Maheshwar (80 kms), glorious city at the dawn of Indian civilization, Today, Maheshwar is also known for its distinctive handwoven sarees called Maheshwari. Proceed to Omkareshwar (55 kms), the sacred island, shaped like the holiest of all Hindu symbols, &#39;Om&#39;, has drawn to it hundreds of generations of pilgrims. Following temple visit Back to Indore Overnight at Indore Hotel.\r\n','','','533669',1,'2014-09-29 12:48:51'),(440,91,'Day 04	:	Depart Bhopal/Indore','Day4_indore_or_bhopal1411975173.jpg','This Day we will Depart to Indore/Bhopal Rly stn/Airport for Back to Home.\r\n','','','627240',1,'2014-09-29 12:49:33'),(441,90,'Day 01	:	Arrive Jabalpur','Day1_marble-rocks-jabalpur1411975250.jpg','Arrive Jabalpur, Pleasure resort and capital of the Gond Kings during the 12th century, Jabalpur was later the seat of the Kalchuri dynasty. Afternoon visit the Marble Rocks at Bhedaghat which rise to a hundred feet on either side of the Narmada. Overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','382827',1,'2014-09-29 12:50:50'),(442,90,'Day 02	:	Jabalpur - Bandhavgarh (164 kms / 3-4 hrs)','Day2_bandavghar1411975283.jpg','Transfer by road to Bandhavgarh, which was known as Shikargah, or game preserve, of the Maharajahs of Rewa and now one of India’s best National Parks famous for Tiger and other wildlife species. Rest of the day at leisure, overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','433087',1,'2014-09-29 12:51:23'),(443,90,'Day 03	:	Bandhavgarh','Day3_at_Bandhavgarh National Park1411975307.jpg','Early morning and evening enjoy a game drive in the Bandhavgarh National Park, you will have an opportunity to see tiger and other wildlife species. The great Gaur, or Indian Bison, can be seen with ease, overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','952037',1,'2014-09-29 12:51:47'),(444,90,'Day 04	:	Bandhavgarh - Khajuraho ( 237 kms/5 - 6 hrs)','Day4_famous Khajuraho temples1411975339.jpg','This morning drive to Khajuraho, The capital of the Chandela Kings, Khajuraho is famous for its magnificent temples dedicated to Lord Shiva, Lord Vishnu and the Jain Tirthankaras. Evening witness a sound & light show at the famous Khajuraho temples, overnight at the hotel\r\n','','','562598',1,'2014-09-29 12:52:19'),(445,90,'Day 05	:	Khajuraho','Day5_at_raneh1411975364.jpg','Visit the World famous Khajuraho temples built by Chandela Kings in the mid-10th and 11th centuries known for its stone carvings and best example of Temple architecture in India. After noon visit to Ranhe water falls, A beautiful picnic spot famous for its granite rock formations. Overnight at the hotel \r\n','','','100403',1,'2014-09-29 12:52:44'),(446,90,'Day 06	:	Khajuraho - Gwalior (375 kms/8-9 hrs)','Day61411984285.jpg','Early this morning you will drive to Gwalior, enroute you will stop to visit Datia known for  its 7 storied palace of Raja Bir Singh Deo & Gopeshwar Temple and Orcha, the most powerful kingdoms of Central India, in the 16th cent. Proceed to your hotel and rest of the day is at leisure, overnight at the hotel.\r\n','','','142186',1,'2014-09-29 15:21:25'),(447,90,'Day 07	:	Gwalior','Day7_jai-vilas-palace-museum1411984312.jpg','Morning proceed for a sightseeing tour of Gwalior, visit the mighty Gwalior Fort, lastly visit the Jai Vilas Palace and museum. Rest of the day at leisure for shopping and individual activities, overnight at the hotel. \r\n','','','408268',1,'2014-09-29 15:21:52'),(448,90,'Day 08	:	Depart Gwalior','Day8_Gwalior1411984343.jpg','Transfer to airport/railway station for your onward journey back home  \r\n','','','507580',1,'2014-09-29 15:22:23'),(449,89,'Day 01  :  Arrive Raipur','Day1_budha-talab-raipur1411984452.jpg','Arrive Raipur, the capital of Chattisgarh & transfer to your hotel. This afternoon proceed on a sightseeing tour of Raipur – visit the Mahamaya Mandir, Boodha Talab & the Guru Ghasidas Museum. Evening at leisure. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','291399',1,'2014-09-29 15:24:12'),(450,89,'Day 02  : Raipur - Bhoramdeao - Raipur','Day2_at_bhoramdeo1411984498.JPG','This morning proceed on a full day excursion to Bhoramdeao (120 kms / 2-3 hrs) to visit the Bhoramdeao Temple built in the period of 7th to 11th Century and carved on the rocky stones in Nagar style. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','470002',1,'2014-09-29 15:24:58'),(451,89,'Day 03  :  Raipur - Sirpur - Barnawapara','Day3_at_Champaran & Rajim1411984549.jpg','Today proceed on an excursion to Sirpur (84 kms/2 hrs). Visit the famous brick structured Laxman Temple, which is one of the finest brick temples in the country. Walk across to the Buddha Vihar, an archeological site where they have excavated the 6th century ruins of the Gupta Dynasty temples. Later drive to Barnawapara, a wild life sanctuary in Chattisgarh. Day at leisure for game viewing in the sanctuary. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','190692',1,'2014-09-29 15:25:49'),(452,0,'','','','','','',1,'2014-09-29 15:27:24'),(453,89,'Day 04  :  Barnawapara - Champaran - Rajim - Jagdalpur','Day4_Laxman_Temple1411984783.JPG','After an early breakfast you will be transferred to Jagdalpur (375 kms/8-9 hrs drive), enroute visit the temples at the Champaran & Rajim. Arrive Jagdalpur & transfer to your hotel. Evening at leisure. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','823832',1,'2014-09-29 15:29:43'),(454,89,'Day 05  :  Jagdalpur - Kanger - Tirathgarh - Jagdalpur','Day5_at_tirathgarh1411984835.jpg','Today you will proceed on a full day excursion with your packed lunch to Kanger Valley national park & Tirathgarh water falls. You will visit the Kutumsar Caves (34 kms/1 hour) with its marvelous stalactites & stalagmites. Later visit the magnificent seven tires Tirathgarh falls. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','626604',1,'2014-09-29 15:30:35'),(455,89,'Day 06  : Jagdalpur - Chitrakoot','Day6_chitrakoot-waterfalls1411984887.jpg','This morning you will visit the Anthropological Museum & visit the near by Nagarnar tribal village where the craftsmen display their skills. You may shop for some excellent handicraft artifacts here. After lunch you will be transferred to the famous Chitrakoot water falls(38 kms/1 hr), where the river Indravati has an abrupt fall of 96 ft. The falls that are like horseshoe curve are often compared to Naigara Falls. Overnight at the log huts overlooking the spectacular Chitrakoot waterfalls.\r\n','','','678777',1,'2014-09-29 15:31:27'),(456,89,'Day 07  :  Chitrakoot - Jagdalpur - Raipur','Day7_Bastar Handicrafts1411984936.jpg','Today transfer to Raipur (300 kms/6-7 hrs), enroute visit Kondagaon village, where you may buy exclusive Bastar Handicrafts. Arrive Raipur and proceed to your hotel. Day is at leisure for shopping and individual activities. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','613013',1,'2014-09-29 15:32:16'),(457,89,'Day 08 :  Depart Raipur','Day8_Raipur1411984976.jpg','Transfer to airport/railway station for your onward journey back home.\r\n','','','633207',1,'2014-09-29 15:32:56'),(458,77,'Day 01	:        Coimbatore - Ooty (90 kms/2-3 hrs)','Day1_ootacamund1411985264.jpg','Arrive Coimbatore.  Transfer by road to Ooty, with its beautiful gardens, wooden rolling hills, pine and eucalyptus forests and cool climate has earned the name the Queen of Hill stations. The rest of the day is at leisure. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','211430',1,'2014-09-29 15:37:44'),(459,77,'Day 02	:	Ooty','Day2_at_Gardens1411985295.JPG','Today you will visit Botanical Gardens, known for its exotic plants and colourfully laid out ornamental gardens, the Doddabetta Peak the highest point in the Nilgiri Mountains, enjoy an optional boat ride on beautiful Ooty Lake. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','516333',1,'2014-09-29 15:38:15'),(460,77,'Day 03	:	Ooty - Kodaikanal (264 kms/7-8 hrs)','Day3_at_kodaikanal1411985323.jpg','This morning you proceed to Kodaikanal,  a charming hill station amidst sylvan beauty on the Southern crest of the upper Palani Hills. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','312779',1,'2014-09-29 15:38:43'),(461,77,'Day 04	:	Kodaikanal','Day4_at_Kodai Lake1411985354.jpg','Today you will visit the Shenbaganur Museum which houses one of the best orchid collections in India, the Coakers Walk on the steep southern face of the Kodai Ridge with its Telescope House and the picturesque Kodai Lake.  Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','308585',1,'2014-09-29 15:39:14'),(462,77,'Day 05	:	Depart Kodaikanal ','Day5_at_REturn1411985384.jpg','Today you will be transferred to Madurai (120 kms/3 hrs)/ Coimbatore (170 kms/4-5 hrs) airport / railway station for onward journey\r\n','','','931720',1,'2014-09-29 15:39:44'),(463,78,'Day 01	:	Arrive Bangalore','Day1_at_labhag1411985510.JPG','Arrive and transfer to your hotel. This afternoon you visit the Lal Baugh Botanical Gardens, the 16th century Bull Temple and drive past the Vidhan Saudha. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','928224',1,'2014-09-29 15:41:50'),(464,0,'','','','','','',1,'2014-09-29 15:43:30'),(465,78,'Day 02	:	Bangalore - Mysore (160 kms / 6-7 hrs)','Day2_at_Nandi_Chamundi_Mysore1411985717.jpg','Transfer by road to Mysore, en-route you visit  the Sri Rangapuram for Lord Sri Ranganathaswamy Temple Also visit to Tippu Sultan Fort\r\nArrive  Check in to Hotel Later visit to Mysore Palace known for its veritable treasure trove of exquisite carvings and works of art from world over, the Chamundi Hills for a panoramic view of Mysore city and the Rajendra Art Gallery which houses some remarkable selections of paintings by Raja Ravi Verma. The evening is at leisure for shopping some of Mysore&#39;s famous silks & fabrics. Also visit to Brundavanamu  Garden Situated at Sri Krishna Devarayala  Project Back to Hotel   Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','369366',1,'2014-09-29 15:45:17'),(466,78,'Day 03	:	Mysore - Ooty (158 kms / 3-4 hrs)','Day3_at_ooty1411985748.jpg','Transfer by road to Ooty, &#39;the Queen of Hill stations&#39;. The rest of the day is at leisure to explore this picturesque hill station. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','627928',1,'2014-09-29 15:45:48'),(467,78,'Day 04	:	Ooty','Day4_at_ooty_lake1411985770.jpg','This morning you visit the Doddabetta Peak, the highest peak in the Nilgiri mountains, the beautifully landscaped Botanical Gardens and the scenic Ooty lake where you may enjoy an optional boat ride. Overnight at hotel.\r\n','','','868063',1,'2014-09-29 15:46:10'),(468,78,'Day 05	:	Depart Ooty ','Day5_at_return_home1411985793.jpg','Transfer to airport / railway station at Coimbatore ( 90 kms/ 2 hrs) or Bangalore ( 290 kms/ 7 hrs).\r\n','','','203866',1,'2014-09-29 15:46:33'),(469,79,'Day 01 : Bangalore - Mysore (160 kms / 6-7 hrs)','Day1_at_gumbaz1411985927.jpg','Transfer by road to Mysore, en-route you may visit  the Srirangapatnam,The Sriranganatha swamy Temple, Also visitto Tippu Sultan Palace ,On