 of Penang was named after King George III of England, is an interesting lend of the old and new. It is worth to note that Penang has one of the largest Colonial Buildings in Southeast Asia. Tours includes a stop at Fort Cornwallis, built in 1808. Fort Cornwallis also marks the spot where Sir Francis Light first landed on this island. You will be driven through Street Harmony, which houses the Anglican Church, Kuan Yin Chinese Temple, Mahamariaman Indian Temple and the Kapitan Keling Mosque. Followed by a visit to the State Museum, built in 1821, which houses a fine collection of old photographs, maps, charts  and  pass  by  the  colourful  Little  India  and  bustling  Chinatown. Next  stop,  the World’s    Fourth    Largest    Reclining    Buddha    statue    at    Wat    Chayamangkalaram.  Dineer at Local Indian Restaurant Hotel Flamingo Beach Resort ***/Central Sea View Penang***','','','740153',1,'2015-02-16 11:20:01'),(590,114,'Day 06:Penang Island-Depart KUL International Airport ','KLIA_MTB&Tower1424065989.jpg','This Day enjoy buffet breakfast at hotel coffee shop,free explore to Penang Island on your Own, visit to local market, proceed to putrajaya tour Lunch at Putra Palace ,In the Evening Depart to KUL International Airport for to back to home with Unlimited Sweet Memories. ','','','322763',1,'2015-02-16 11:23:09'),(591,4,'Day 08 :Arrival - Delhi - Srinagar (120 Kms/ 4 hrs)','devprayag1428492100.jpg','Morning arrival at Delhi (05:00 AM). here tour ends here with happy memories to be cherished forever.','','Morning arrival at Delhi (05:00 AM). here tour ends here with happy memories to be cherished forever.','366182',1,'2015-04-08 16:51:40'),(592,4,'HOTEL INFORMATION','plain-image1428510589.jpg','<table border=\"1 solid black;\" CELLSPACING=\"0\" style=\"width:100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>City</th>\r\n<th>Standard Hotel/ similar</th>\r\n<th>No of Nights</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Srinagar</td>\r\n<td>Srikot Castle</td>\r\n<td>01</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\